0to%20art%20school%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20France%2C%20going%20to%20university%20is%20relatively%20inexpensive%20because%20tuition%20is%20subsidized%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20pressured%20to%20pick%20a%20university%20like%20my%20friends%20but%20I%20struggled%20to%20choose%20a%20degree%20because%20I%20had%20so%20many%20interests.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20considered%20studying%20philosophy%20or%20literature.%20Art%20school%20was%20also%20an%20option%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20an%20artist%2C%20but%20I'd%20heard%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20get%20a%20job%20after%20an%20art%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20travel%2C%20so%20I%20settled%20on%20a%20private%20six-month%20flight%20attendant%20degree%2C%20funded%20through%20a%20loan%20from%20my%20parents.%20It%20was%20very%20different%20from%20a%20university%20course.%20Our%20classes%20were%20in%20a%20hotel's%20convention%20room%20and%20a%20training%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20become%20a%20flight%20attendant%20after%20completing%20the%20course.%20Instead%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-australia-no-regrets-cheaper-sunshine-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20began%20traveling%20and%20doing%20odd%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20traveling%20through%20different%20countries%20for%20around%20six%20years%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20France%20in%202018.%20I%20had%20been%20working%20in%20retail%20in%20Canada%20and%20wasn't%20feeling%20fulfilled.%20I%20considered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-welder-blue-collar-work-earning-getting-fit-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20in%20a%20skill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20knew%20I%20liked%20to%20create%20things%2C%20so%20I%20looked%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconstruction-jobs-housing-skilled-trades-infrastructure-electricians-future-work-opportunities-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econstruction%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20woodworking%20paths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20enrolled%20in%20a%20yearlong%20boatbuilding%20course%2C%20which%20was%20free%20because%20the%20government%20subsidized%20it.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20a%20full-time%20boatbuilder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20somewhat%20sad%20I%20missed%20out%20on%20the%20university%20experience.%20I%20would%20have%20enjoyed%20attending%20lectures%20and%20living%20in%20a%20dorm.%20But%20I'm%20happy%20with%20the%20choice%20I%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7cd8701-b1f3-4676-a979-4407dde47345%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20can%20see%20myself%20progressing%20in%20my%20boatbuilding%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20course%2C%20we%20built%20a%20kayak%20and%20Norweigian%20Pram%2C%20a%20small%20clinker%20boat%2C%20to%20learn%20the%20different%20stages%20of%20building%2C%20like%20making%20frames%20and%20varnishing.%20It%20gave%20me%20an%20understanding%20of%20a%20boatbuilding%20job%2C%20but%20I%20was%20still%20inexperienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20multiple%20work%20placements%20as%20part%20of%20the%20course.%20I%20did%20a%20three-week%20placement%20in%20Portsmouth%2C%20England.%20They%20asked%20me%20to%20come%20back%20and%20work%20with%20them%20as%20a%20shipwright%20%E2%80%94%20working%20on%20wooden%20boats%20%E2%80%94%20when%20the%20course%20was%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20restoring%20and%20building%20sailing%20boats.%20When%20I%20started%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20knew%20nothing%2C%20but%20thankfully%2C%20I%20was%20surrounded%20by%20people%20willing%20to%20train%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20the%20only%20woman%20in%20the%20workshop%2C%20which%20was%20a%20very%20male%20environment.%20My%20first%20reaction%20was%20to%20mimic%20their%20behavior.%20We%20had%20good%20fun%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20wasn't%20being%20myself.%20I'm%20passionate%20about%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20women%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20in%20that%20job%20for