ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-whatsapp-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bots%20were%20also%20given%20their%20own%20Instagram%20pages%2C%20which%20now%20appear%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCxu7BwILhlf%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26ig_rid%3D3ad2e55c-8751-4056-9b28-8265029e03cc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20taken%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20reportedly%20paid%20creators%20to%20use%20their%20likeness%20for%20over%20two%20years%2C%20meaning%20they%20have%20cut%20the%20contracts%20short.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20from%20The%20Information%20published%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Meta%20paid%20one%20unnamed%20top%20creator%20as%20much%20as%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-paying-celebrity-faces-of-ai-chatbots-as-much-as-5-million-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%245%20million%20over%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20six%20hours%20of%20work%20in%20a%20studio%20to%20use%20their%20likeness%20as%20an%20AI%20assistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20retreat%20from%20the%20celebrity-inspired%20chatbots%20shows%20how%20difficult%20it%20has%20been%20for%20tech%20companies%20to%20develop%20successful%20generative%20AI%20products.%20After%20the%20initial%20success%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20Big%20Tech%20rushed%20to%20release%20a%20flood%20of%20AI-powered%20products%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20met%20with%20a%20muted%20reaction%20from%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology's%20hype%20has%20attracted%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20investment%2C%20and%20companies%20have%20responded%20by%20spending%20big%20on%20development.%20However%2C%20it's%20still%20unclear%20whether%20AI%20can%20generate%20enough%20returns%20to%20match%20the%20hype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Meta's%20case%2C%20investors%20are%20apparently%20still%20prepared%20to%20forgive%20the%20company's%20high%20AI%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday's%20earnings%20call%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20Meta%20would%20keep%20spending%20big%20this%20year%20to%20support%20AI%20research%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-spending-more-mark-zuckerberg-investors-stock-price-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20was%20rewarded%20with%20a%20stock%20rise%20of%20nearly%207%25%20after%20hours.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scraps-kendall-jenner-tom-brady-celebrity-ai-chatbots-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722506433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ab5c41aab37011780c4fd1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scraps-kendall-jenner-tom-brady-celebrity-ai-chatbots-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta%20is%20shifting%20focus%20to%20its%20new%20AI%20Studio%2C%20which%20lets%20users%20create%20their%20own%20AI%20bots.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scraps-kendall-jenner-tom-brady-celebrity-ai-chatbots-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%20has%20kept%20its%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20secret.%20Until%20now.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Black%20rectangle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa7ede1a227600e63333e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20reported%20in%20partnership%20with%20The%20Trace%20and%20Type%20Investigations.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENemesia%20Martinez%20was%20working%20at%20one%20of%20Mississippi's%20dozens%20of%20poultry%20plants%20on%20July%2020%2C%202016%2C%20when%20she%20missed%20a%20call%20from%20her%20neighbor.%20It%20was%209%20p.m.%2C%20and%20her%20shift%20defeathering%20and%20extracting%20the%20livers%20from%20chickens%2C%20at%20a%20facility%20about%20an%20hour%20outside%20Jackson%2C%20wouldn't%20end%20until%2010%3A30.%20But%20Martinez%20had%20a%20feeling%20something%20was%20off.%20When%20she%20went%20to%20the%20bathroom%20to%20call%20back%2C%20her%20neighbor%20told%20her%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20police%20at%20your%20home.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartinez%2C%20now%2047%2C%20shared%20the%20modest%20ranch-style%20house%20with%20her%20partner%2C%20Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%2C%2048%2C%20and%20a%20few%20housemates.%20She%20and%20Ramos%20had%20landed%20in%20Laurel%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20earlier%2C%20attracted%20by%20the%20plentiful%20if%20grueling%20poultry%20work%2C%20and%20had%20built%20a%20stable%20life%20for%20themselves.%20But%20they%20were%20both%20unauthorized%20immigrants%2C%20and%20the%20threat%20of%20arrest%20by%20immigration%20officials%20was%20a%20part%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartinez%20arrived%20home%20at%20about%2011%20o'clock%2C%20filled%20with%20trepidation.%20There%2C%20she%20saw%20a%20patrol%20car%20and%20a%20white%20van%20along%20with%20three%20agents%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20was%20wearing%20a%20vest%20from%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement.%20Like%20every%20poultry%20worker%20in%20Laurel%20with%20her%20immigration%20status%2C%20Martinez%20had%20heard%20about%20the%20agency's%20raids%20and%20deportations%20and%20knew%20how%20to%20recognize%20and%20avoid%20its%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnxious%20that%20Ramos%20had%20been%20arrested%2C%20and%20worried%20about%20risking%20arrest%20herself%2C%20she%20turned%20around%20and%20headed%20to%20a%20friend's%20place%20to%20spend%20the%20night.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20afraid%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Ramos%20wasn't%20picking%20up%20his%20phone%2C%20and%20she%20struggled%20to%20get%20to%20sleep%20that%20night%2C%20not%20knowing%20what%20had%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20news%20of%20a%20shooting%20in%20Laurel%20began%20circulating%20on%20Facebook%20and%20WhatsApp.%20Friends%20began%20messaging%20Soledad%20Ramos%20Hernandez%2C%20Ramos's%20younger%20sister%2C%20to%20send%20condolences%2C%20assuming%20her%20brother%20had%20been%20killed.%20That's%20how%20Soledad%20first%20got%20wind%20that%20her%20brother%20might%20have%20been%20shot.%20She%20had%20no%20idea%20where%20he%20was%2C%20or%20whether%20he%20was%20even%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20am%20I%20supposed%20to%20tell%20my%20parents%20if%20he%20died%3F%26quot%3B%20Soledad%20remembered%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Soledad%20Hernandez%20in%20a%20black%20hoodie%2C%20Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%20in%20a%20blue%20T-shirt%2C%20and%20Soledad%20Ramos%20Hernandez%20in%20a%20flowered%20blouse.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a147b380d4d5da13d6d526%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222367%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%2C%20center%2C%20with%20his%20sister%2C%20Soledad%20Ramos%20Hernandez%2C%20right%2C%20and%20his%20partner%2C%20Nemesia%20Martinez%2C%20left%2C%20in%20their%20home%20in%20Laurel%2C%20Mississippi.%3Cp%3ETimothy%20Ivy%20for%20The%20Trace%20and%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EApproximately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F11%2F16%2Fwhat-we-know-about-unauthorized-immigrants-living-in-the-us%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHere%2520are%2520some%2520additional%2520findings%2Cworkers%252C%2520a%2520relatively%2520narrow%2520range.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20in%20every%2020%3C%2Fa%3E%20US%20workers%20is%20unauthorized%2C%20and%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20threatened%20to%20enact%20mass%20deportations%20of%20those%20workers%20and%20their%20families%20if%20he%20is%20again%20elected%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20when%20and%20how%20ICE%20agents%20use%20deadly%20force%20has%20long%20been%20shrouded%20in%20secrecy.%20Last%20year%2C%20a%20federal%20oversight%20agency%20found%20that%20ICE%20had%20failed%20to%20thoroughly%20documents%20its%20use-of-force%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%20unreported%20bodycam%20footage%20and%20documents%20related%20to%20Ramos's%20encounter%20with%20ICE%20agents%20that%20day%20in%20July%202016%20offer%20an%20unusual%20window%20into%20the%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20by%20immigration%20agents%2C%20and%20what%20happens%20in%20the%20aftermath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20records%20obtained%20through%20litigation%20show%20that%20Ramos's%20shooting%20was%20not%20an%20isolated%20case.%20It%20was%20one%20of%2059%20shootings%20by%20ICE%20officers%20from%202015%20to%202021%20that%20took%20place%20across%2026%20states%20and%20two%20US%20territories%2C%20including%20two%20that%20were%20self-inflicted.%20At%20least%2024%20people%20were%20injured%20in%20the%20shootings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-three%20were%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20first%20comprehensive%20look%20at%20ICE%20shootings%20across%20the%20country%2C%20a%20collaboration%20among%20Business%20Insider%2C%20The%20Trace%2C%20and%20Type%20Investigations%2C%20shows%20that%20several%20incidents%20went%20unexamined%20and%20others%20appear%20to%20have%20violated%20the%20agency's%20own%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use-of-force%20logs%20we%20obtained%20are%20bare-bones%20and%20selectively%20redacted.%20They%20include%20the%20location%20and%20the%20date%20of%20the%20shooting%20and%20list%20injuries%20and%20deaths.%20But%20they%20don't%20include%20agent%20or%20victim%20names%20or%20narrative%20details.%20We've%20pieced%20together%20additional%20details%20from%20police%20departments%2C%20prosecutors%2C%20police%20and%20court%20records%2C%20an%20inspector-general%20report%2C%20and%20local%20media%20coverage.%20We%20could%20not%20identify%20supplemental%20records%20for%2018%20of%20these%20shootings%20that%20might%20have%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20circumstances%20surrounding%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221318%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20partially%20redacted%20ICE%20log%20that%20includes%20the%20headings%20LEO%20Information%20and%20Suspect%20%2F%20Subject%20Information%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a13f662d66759f66fdde91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EICE%20closely%20holds%20its%20use-of-force%20logs.%20This%20one%2C%20obtained%20through%20a%20public%20records%20request%2C%20documents%20a%20shooting%20fatality%20that%20took%20place%20on%20February%2023%2C%202018%20in%20Woodbridge%2C%20Virginia.%3Cp%3EImmigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20shootings%20posed%20considerable%20risks%20to%20bystanders.%20ICE%20agents%20shot%20people%20in%20public%20places%2C%20such%20as%20traffic%20intersections%20and%20strip-mall%20parking%20lots.%20They%20fired%20their%20weapons%20at%20moving%20vehicles.%20In%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20cases%2C%20we%20uncovered%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20the%20shooting%20victims%20were%20unarmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20full%20list%20of%20incidents%20has%20never%20been%20publicly%20reported%20by%20ICE.%20And%20if%20any%20of%20the%20officers%20who%20fired%20their%20weapons%20were%20disciplined%2C%20ICE%20has%20kept%20that%20secret%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%20has%20even%20refused%20to%20release%20its%20current%20use-of-force%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%20agents%20are%20assigned%20to%20either%20civil%20immigration%20enforcement%20%E2%80%94%20detaining%20and%20deporting%20unauthorized%20immigrants%20like%20Ramos%20%E2%80%94%20or%20criminal%20investigations.%20The%20latter%20are%20led%20by%20Homeland%20Security%20Investigations%2C%20a%20division%20of%20ICE%20that%20partners%20with%20other%20law-enforcement%20agencies%20to%20investigate%20cross-border%20crimes%20ranging%20from%20drugs%20and%20weapons%20smuggling%20to%20financial%20crimes.%20A%20large%20proportion%20of%20the%20shootings%20we%20uncovered%20involved%20HSI%20agents%2C%20and%20some%20occurred%20during%20genuinely%20risky%20operations%20such%20as%20undercover%20drug%20busts%20or%20multi-agency%20raids%20targeting%20human-trafficking%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20in%20over%20half%20of%20the%20shootings%20we%20identified%2C%20ICE%20agents%20never%20made%20an%20arrest.%20In%20at%20least%20seven%20cases%2C%20the%20person%20shot%20by%20an%20ICE%20officer%20was%20not%20the%20target%20of%20the%20enforcement%20action.%20Eleven%20shootings%20occurred%20while%20officers%20were%20off-duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-chart-id%3D%5C%22recklessness%5C%22%20data-chart-theme%3D%5C%22bi%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20agents%2C%20ICE%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20federal%20law-enforcement%20bodies%20in%20the%20country%2C%20bigger%20than%20any%20local%20police%20department%20other%20than%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Police%20Department.%20Yet%20many%20other%20large%20law-enforcement%20agencies%20have%20more%20independent%20oversight%20than%20ICE.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Police%20Department%2C%20which%20employs%20about%209%2C000%20officers%2C%20has%20an%20internal-affairs%20division%2C%20a%20professional%20standards%20bureau%2C%20an%20independent%20board%20of%20police%20commissioners%2C%20and%20an%20inspector%20general%20to%20investigate%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20ICE%2C%20oversight%20of%20misconduct%20is%20fragmented.%20It's%20handled%20sometimes%20by%20ICE%2C%20sometimes%20by%20ICE's%20parent%20agency%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%2C%20and%20sometimes%20primarily%20by%20local%20law%20enforcement%20with%20jurisdiction%20in%20the%20location%20where%20an%20incident%20took%20place.%20The%20results%20of%20ICE's%20internal%20investigations%20are%20not%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20a%20single%20shooting%20we%20examined%20resulted%20in%20an%20indictment%20anywhere%20in%20the%20country%2C%20even%20in%20instances%20when%20ICE's%20narrative%20of%20a%20shooting%20was%20contradicted%20by%20video%20footage.%20In%20some%20of%20these%20cases%2C%20ICE%20agents%20hindered%20investigations%20by%20violating%20protocols.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChuck%20Wexler%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20nonprofit%20Police%20Executive%20Research%20Forum%2C%20says%20federal%20agencies%20haven't%20faced%20a%20%26quot%3Breckoning%26quot%3B%20about%20use%20of%20force%20the%20way%20municipal%20police%20departments%20have%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EGenerally%20speaking%2C%20there's%20a%20big%20difference%2C%20a%20huge%20difference%2C%20between%20what%20federal%20law%20enforcement%20does%20and%20what%20municipal%20law%20enforcement%20does%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%20has%20admitted%20to%20wrongful%20use%20of%20firearms%20only%20once%20since%202016%2C%20after%20an%20ICE%20agent%20accidentally%20fired%20his%20weapon%20during%20an%20apartment%20search.%20No%20one%20was%20injured.%20The%20person%20of%20interest%20was%20not%20there%2C%20but%20ICE%20conducted%20an%20impromptu%20arrest%20of%20someone%20else%20on%20the%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenia%20Blaser%2C%20an%20attorney%20with%20the%20New%20York%20nonprofit%20Immigrant%20Defense%20Project%2C%20described%20the%20cases%20we%20examined%20as%20being%20part%20of%20a%20long-standing%20pattern%20of%20unnecessary%20escalation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20regularly%20seen%20that%20ICE%20tactics%20and%20arrests%20themselves%20created%20violence%2C%20and%20how%20quickly%20ICE%20agents%20escalate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20kicking%20down%20doors%20to%20holding%20people%20at%20gunpoint%20in%20front%20of%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiguel%20Alvarez%2C%20an%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20respond%20on%20the%20record%20to%20detailed%20queries%20about%20our%20investigative%20findings%2C%20including%20whether%20any%20ICE%20agents%20have%20been%20disciplined%20over%20their%20use%20of%20deadly%20force.%20But%20he%20said%20ICE%20agents%20operate%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20utmost%20integrity%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bleadership%20across%20the%20agency%20and%20department%20further%20reinforce%20standards%20of%20ethical%20and%20responsible%20conduct%20to%20further%20build%20and%20maintain%20public%20trust.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BICE's%20mission%20brings%20an%20authority%20to%20use%20force%20when%20necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20Alvarez%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BAuthorized%20law%20enforcement%20officials%20are%20highly%20trained%20to%20only%20use%20force%20as%20a%20last%20resort%20when%20objectively%20reasonable%20and%20necessary%2C%20and%20to%20leverage%20de-escalation%20tactics.%20ICE%20personnel%20are%20regularly%20re-trained%2C%20and%20required%20to%20be%20familiar%20with%20all%20applicable%20directives%2C%20guidance%2C%20and%20policy%20and%20take%20appropriate%20action%20to%20comply%20with%20relevant%20laws%20and%20procedures.%20Any%20deviation%20or%20violation%20is%20investigated%20thoroughly%2C%20and%20if%20substantiated%2C%20disciplinary%20and%2For%20other%20appropriate%20actions%20are%20taken.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20siblings%20in%20Puebla%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Ramos%20only%20finished%20the%20fourth%20grade.%20He%20knew%20from%20childhood%20that%20he%20would%20probably%20follow%20the%20path%20laid%20by%20his%20older%20cousins%20and%20move%20to%20Mississippi%20to%20work%20in%20a%20poultry%20plant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20he%20tried%20to%20cross%20into%20the%20United%20States%2C%20at%20age%2023%2C%20he%20was%20caught%20by%20Border%20Patrol.%20The%20final%20time%20he%20tried%2C%20in%202002%2C%20carrying%20only%20a%20change%20of%20clothes%20and%20a%20bottle%20of%20water%2C%20he%20crossed%20through%20the%20desert%20into%20Arizona%20and%20made%20his%20way%20to%20Phoenix%2C%20where%20his%20cousins%20picked%20him%20up%20and%20drove%20him%20to%20southeastern%20Mississippi.%20There%2C%20he%20found%20work%20at%20a%20poultry%20plant%20in%20Laurel%2C%20about%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20outside%20Jackson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spent%20years%20jumping%20between%20the%20poultry%20plant%20and%20other%20day%20work%2C%20earning%20enough%20to%20send%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20to%20his%20family%20back%20home%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20account%20of%20what%20happened%20to%20Ramos%20that%20summer%20evening%20in%202016%20is%20based%20on%20body-camera%20footage%2C%20ICE%20incident%20and%20investigation%20reports%2C%20a%20DHS%20inspector%20general%20report%2C%20a%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20the%20ICE%20agent%2C%20court%20depositions%2C%20reports%20from%20the%20Laurel%20Police%20Department%20and%20the%20Mississippi%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20and%20interviews%20with%20Ramos%2C%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20his%20sister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20evening%2C%20Ramos%20stopped%20by%20a%20friend's%20home%20in%20Laurel%20for%20a%20birthday%20party.%20After%20having%20several%20beers%2C%20he%20and%20his%20then%20housemate%20each%20got%20in%20their%20cars%20for%20the%20drive%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%20stands%20on%20a%20country%20road%20in%20Mississippi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a1486dfb2b6bedb05a2fdf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222403%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERamos%20stands%20at%20the%20spot%20on%20the%20street%20near%20his%20Laurel%20home%20where%20he%20was%20shot%20by%20ICE%20agents%20in%202016.%3Cp%3ETimothy%20Ivy%20for%20The%20Trace%20and%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20subsequent%20deposition%20by%20a%20Laurel%20police%20officer%2C%20Jake%20Driskell%2C%20he%20and%20another%20officer%20saw%20Ramos%20and%20his%20housemate%20roll%20through%20a%20stop%20sign.%20They%20suspected%20that%20the%20housemate%2C%20who%20was%20driving%20behind%20Ramos%20in%20a%20white%20Nissan%2C%20was%20intoxicated%20and%20pulled%20him%20over%20in%20a%20grassy%20driveway%20behind%20the%20home%20he%20shared%20with%20Ramos.%20Ramos%20pulled%20over%2C%20too.%20The%20men%20stepped%20out%20of%20their%20cars%2C%20and%20Driskell%20asked%20the%20housemate%20a%20few%20questions%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20speak%20English%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20ID%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVideo%20shows%20that%20within%20minutes%2C%20Driskell%20walked%20back%20to%20his%20squad%20car%20and%20called%20nearby%20ICE%20agents%20to%20the%20scene.%20Laurel%20police%20officers%20described%20Ramos%20as%20%26quot%3Bmouthy%26quot%3B%20and%20asked%20for%20Spanish%20translation%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20immigration%20officers%20arrived%2C%20Ramos%20recognized%20them%20as%20ICE%20and%20bolted%2C%20running%20around%20to%20the%20street%20in%20front%20of%20his%20home.%20An%20ICE%20agent%2C%20Phillip%20Causey%2C%20ran%20after%20him%2C%20yelling%20at%20him%20to%20stop.%20%26quot%3BBaja!%26quot%3B%20(Down!)%20Causey%20can%20be%20heard%20yelling.%20%26quot%3BGet%20down!%20Get%20on%20the%20fucking%20ground!%20Get%20the%20fuck%20down!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScared%20and%20confused%2C%20Ramos%20gave%20up%20and%20stopped%20running%2C%20according%20to%20a%20subsequent%20civil%20complaint.%20He%20turned%20around%20and%20walked%20back%20toward%20the%20agents.%20When%20Causey%20ordered%20Ramos%20to%20put%20his%20hands%20up%2C%20according%20to%20Ramos'%20complaint%2C%20he%20lifted%20one%20into%20the%20air%2C%20using%20the%20other%20to%20hold%20up%20his%20falling%20pants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20Causey%20shot%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fuzzy%20body%20cam%20footage%20showing%20a%20car%20and%20a%20cell%20phone%2C%20left%2C%20and%20a%20man%20bloodied%20on%20the%20pavement%2C%20right%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a1433980d4d5da13d6d1ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBody%20cam%20footage%20shows%20a%20Laurel%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20police%20officer%20calling%20ICE%20for%20translation%20assistance%20after%20pulling%20over%20Ramos'%20housemate%2C%20left.%20Ramos%20moments%20after%20being%20shot%20by%20ICE%20agents%2C%20right.%3Cp%3ELaurel%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERamos%20wasn't%20the%20target%20of%20the%20police%20stop.%20And%20neither%20he%20nor%20his%20housemate%20was%20the%20target%20of%20an%20immigration%20enforcement%20action.%20But%20Ramos%20still%20became%20one%20of%20dozens%20of%20people%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20an%20ICE%20agent's%20deadly%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECausey's%20bullet%20penetrated%20Ramos's%20arm%2C%20hitting%20bone.%20Another%20officer's%20body%20camera%20appears%20to%20show%20him%20running%20toward%20Ramos.%20In%20an%20otherwise%20pitch-black%20street%2C%20the%20officer's%20flashlight%20shows%20Ramos%20writhing%20in%20pain%2C%20bleeding%20onto%20the%20black%20asphalt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20shouldn't%20have%20went%20for%20your%20pockets%2C%26quot%3B%20Causey%20yelled%20at%20Ramos%20as%20he%20crouched%20over%20him%2C%20putting%20pressure%20on%20the%20wound.%20Soon%2C%20eight%20officers%20stood%20around%20Ramos%2C%20a%20mix%20of%20ICE%20agents%20and%20Laurel%20police%20officers%2C%20as%20his%20plaid%20shirt%20became%20saturated%20with%20blood.%20%26quot%3BMe%20no%20hear%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramos%20said%2C%20in%20between%20shrieks%20of%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20tried%20to%20remove%20Ramos's%20shirt%20to%20access%20the%20wound%20and%20provide%20first%20aid%20as%20he%20twisted%20and%20thrashed.%20When%20they%20rolled%20him%20on%20his%20side%20looking%20for%20signs%20of%20other%20injuries%2C%20Ramos%20screamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20lay%20on%20the%20asphalt%20until%20an%20ambulance%20arrived%20and%20paramedics%20loaded%20him%20onto%20a%20gurney.%20%26quot%3BPlease%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20groaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE%20agents%20have%20shot%20other%20unarmed%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20February%202018%20shooting%20in%20Dumfries%2C%20Virginia%2C%20an%20ICE%20agent%2C%20who%20was%20a%20member%20of%20a%20US%20Marshals%20fugitive%20task%20force%2C%20killed%20an%20unarmed%20man%20named%20Mario%20Bass%20by%20shooting%20him%20as%20he%20was%20fleeing%20arrest.%20The%20commonwealth's%20attorney's%20office%20began%20to%20investigate%20but%20abruptly%20stopped%2C%20saying%20it%20lacked%20jurisdiction%2C%20and%20wrote%20an%20opinion%20saying%20the%20ICE%20agent%20enjoyed%20immunity%20from%20state%20prosecution%20while%20acting%20as%20a%20federal%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20turned%20over%20to%20the%20FBI%2C%20the%20attorney's%20office%20told%20us%2C%20but%20the%20Justice%20Department%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries%20about%20whether%20it%20had%20investigated.%20Bass'%20family%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20commonwealth's%20attorney%20saying%20that%20by%20failing%20to%20prosecute%20the%20ICE%20agent%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20endangered%20the%20lives%20of%20every%20citizen%20in%20the%20county%20of%20Prince%20William%20and%20the%20larger%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202019%20in%20Nashville%2C%20a%20deportation%20agent%20shot%20at%20a%20man%20twice%20as%20he%20drove%20a%20truck%20out%20of%20a%20grocery-store%20parking%20lot%20that%20has%20heavy%20foot%20traffic.%20An%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20Bryan%20Cox%2C%20told%20reporters%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20wheel%20drove%20toward%20the%20agents.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newschannel5.com%2Fnews%2Fpolice-respond-to-shots-fired-call-at-antioch-food-lion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVideo%20footage%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20by%20a%20local%20TV%20station%20shows%20that%20the%20truck%20was%20parked%20when%20the%20ICE%20agents%20drove%20up%20and%20then%20shows%20the%20agent%2C%20later%20identified%20as%20Bradley%20Epley%2C%20drawing%20his%20gun%20and%20giving%20chase%20as%20the%20truck%20pulls%20away.%20Epley%20then%20fires%20a%20shot%20through%20one%20of%20the%20truck's%20windows.%20The%20FBI%2C%20which%20was%20tasked%20with%20investigating%20an%20attempted-assault%20allegation%20against%20the%20driver%2C%20declined%20to%20charge%20the%20driver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20this%20incident%2C%20or%20any%20other%20shooting%20incident%2C%20including%20whether%20the%20agent%20involved%20was%20disciplined.%20He%20also%20said%20ICE%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20investigations%20or%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS's%202018%20use-of-force%20policy%20says%20that%20shooting%20to%20disable%20a%20moving%20vehicle%20is%20prohibited.%20But%20the%20Nashville%20incident%20was%20one%20of%2018%20shootings%20we%20identified%20that%20appear%20to%20have%20involved%20a%20moving%20vehicle%2C%20including%20several%20car%20chases.%20These%20shootings%20were%20connected%20to%20at%20least%20nine%20deaths%20and%20six%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use-of-force%20policy%20says%20agents%20should%20try%20to%20place%20the%20public%20in%20as%20little%20danger%20as%20possible%20when%20discharging%20a%20weapon.%20Yet%20in%20many%20of%20the%20incidents%20we%20reviewed%2C%20agents%20may%20have%20put%20civilian%20safety%20at%20risk.%20Twenty-one%20shootings%20took%20place%20in%20public%20spaces%2C%20such%20as%20parking%20lots%20or%20traffic%20intersections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202017%20in%20Denver%2C%20a%20deportation%20officer%20named%20Rueben%20Coray%20fired%20once%20at%20Hector%20Santana-Arreola%2C%20grazing%20his%20forehead%2C%20after%20he%20fled%20a%20traffic%20stop%20at%20a%20commercial%20intersection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Denver%20district%20attorney%20later%20said%20that%20Santana%2C%20who%20was%20wanted%20on%20two%20felony%20warrants%2C%20had%20a%20knife%20in%20his%20hand%20within%20arm's%20reach%20of%20the%20officers.%20Santana%20was%20charged%20with%20first-degree%20assault%3B%20the%20Denver%20DA's%20office%20decided%20not%20to%20indict%20the%20ICE%20officer%20who%20shot%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20July%202018%20shooting%20in%20Phoenix%20appeared%20to%20be%20among%20the%20most%20dangerous%20to%20passersby.%20Agents%20engaging%20in%20a%20narcotics%20operation%20opened%20fire%20in%20a%20commercial%20parking%20lot%20lined%20with%20shops%20and%20an%20urgent-care%20facility.%20The%20agents%20shot%20at%20the%20driver%20at%20least%20twice%2C%20injuring%20him.%20ICE%20offered%20inconsistent%20explanations%20for%20the%20shooting.%20An%20ICE%20spokesperson%20told%20local%20reporters%20that%20agents%20fired%20their%20weapons%20after%20a%20driver%20tried%20to%20%26quot%3Bram%20them%20with%20a%20vehicle.%26quot%3B%20But%20an%20ICE%20log%2C%20which%20we%20obtained%2C%20says%20agents%20noted%20the%20suspect%20had%20a%20handgun.%20(The%20log%20made%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20vehicle%20being%20used%20as%20a%20weapon.)%20The%20man%20who%20was%20shot%20acknowledged%20having%20a%20handgun%20in%20the%20car%20but%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Phoenix%20police%20investigators%20that%20he%20didn't%20point%20it%20at%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20store%20clerk%20who%20witnessed%20the%20shooting%20told%20local%20media%20they%20saw%20the%20police%20remove%20a%20young%20boy%20who'd%20been%20sitting%20in%20the%20car's%20passenger%20seat.%20The%204-year-old%2C%20the%20son%20of%20the%20man's%20girlfriend%2C%20was%20injured%20by%20shards%20of%20the%20windshield%20shot%20out%20by%20one%20of%20the%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaricopa%20County%20prosecutors%20later%20said%20the%20agents%20did%20not%20provide%20statements%20until%20nine%20days%20after%20the%20shooting%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20protocol.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20prosecutors%20said%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20for%20the%20agents%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bfully%20cleared%20of%20any%20wrongdoing.%26quot%3B%20They%20did%20not%20recommend%20criminal%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20incident%20in%20a%20commercial%20parking%20lot%2C%20an%20undercover%20drug%20sting%20gone%20awry%20in%20Mesa%2C%20Arizona%2C%20in%20May%202018%2C%20agents%20shot%20a%20suspect%2017%20times.%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20agents%20and%20Maricopa%20County%20sheriff's%20deputies%20who%20were%20also%20part%20of%20the%20mission%20didn't%20fire%20a%20single%20shot.%20The%20Maricopa%20County%20Attorney's%20Office%2C%20which%20investigated%20the%20incident%2C%20did%20not%20recommend%20any%20charges%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20number%20of%20the%20shootings%20documented%20in%20the%20logs%20happened%20while%20ICE%20agents%20were%20off-duty%20or%20in%20plain%20clothes.%20At%20least%20two%20occurred%20during%20attempted%20robberies%2C%20but%20others%20were%20provoked%20by%20far%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Lithia%20Springs%2C%20Georgia%2C%20in%20February%202019%2C%20an%20off-duty%20ICE%20agent%2C%20Othello%20Jones%2C%20pulled%20into%20a%20Walmart%20parking%20lot%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20three%20kids.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.11alive.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Fno-charges-will-be-filed-against-ice-officer-who-shot-killed-man-in-walmart-parking-lot%2F85-68a90343-b8b7-400b-a8ad-95d4164701f7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESurveillance%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20captures%20Jones%20stepping%20out%20of%20his%20car%20and%20pointing%20his%20gun%20at%20another%20car%20as%20it%20pulls%20into%20the%20spot%20next%20to%20his.%20His%20wife%20called%20911%2C%20saying%20the%20man%20in%20the%20other%20car%20had%20followed%20them%20and%20had%20a%20gun.%20In%20a%20matter%20of%20moments%2C%20Jones%20shot%20the%20man%20in%20the%20chest%2C%20killing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20victim%2C%20later%20identified%20as%2045-year-old%20Johnathan%20Liddell%2C%20did%20have%20a%20weapon%20in%20the%20vehicle%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pellet%20gun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20County%20prosecutors%20declined%20to%20press%20charges.%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20a%20justified%20shooting%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20District%20Attorney%20Ryan%20Leonard%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20held%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20later%2C%20arguing%20that%20Jones%20had%20faced%20a%20reasonable%20threat.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20that%20he%20did%20is%20criminal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20ICE%20agents%20operated%20under%20an%20interim%20use-of-force%20policy%2C%20which%20the%20DHS%20Inspector%20General's%20Office%20said%20was%20outdated%20and%20didn't%20incorporate%20lessons%20learned%20since%20its%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20May%202022%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20signed%20an%20executive%20order%20mandating%20that%20DHS%20update%20its%20use-of-force%20policies%20to%20align%20with%20new%20standards%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS%20updated%20the%20use-of-force%20policy%20in%20February%202023%20and%20instructed%20all%20of%20its%20agencies%2C%20including%20ICE%2C%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20ICE%20confirmed%20that%20it%20had%20created%20a%20new%20policy%20in%202023%20but%20refused%20to%20release%20it%20to%20us%2C%20saying%20the%20policies%20had%20%26quot%3Bnot%20been%20published%20for%20public%20view%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20the%20policy%20meets%20or%20exceeds%20DHS%20policy%20in%20all%20material%20respects.%20ICE%20did%20later%20publish%20the%20policy%20document%20%E2%80%94%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ice.gov%2Fdoclib%2Ffoia%2Fpolicy%2F19009.3_firearmsUOF.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20but%20two%20sentences%20fully%20redacted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mostly%20redacted%20document%20titled%20U.S.%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%20-%20ICE%20Directive%2019009.2%3A%20Firearms%20and%20Use%20of%20Force%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a179a8fb2b6bedb05a559d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22706%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EICE%20eventually%20made%20public%20its%202004%20Use%20of%20Force%20Policy%2C%20with%20all%20but%20the%20first%20sentence%20redacted.%3Cp%3EImmigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EC%C3%A9sar%20Cuauht%C3%A9moc%20Garc%C3%ADa%20Ramos%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20civil%20rights%20and%20liberties%20at%20Ohio%20State%20University%20Moritz%20College%20of%20Law%2C%20said%20it's%20%26quot%3Bnext%20to%20impossible%26quot%3B%20to%20access%20ICE's%20use-of-force%20policies%20because%20no%20law%20requires%20it.%20He%20also%20said%20the%20agency's%20policies%20are%20unlikely%20to%20evolve%20until%20they're%20made%20public.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20they're%20operating%20because%20they're%20hiding%20it%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20that%20democratic%20oversight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20what%20your%20starting%20point%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20ICE%20handbook%20from%202021%20sheds%20some%20light%20on%20the%20procedures%20agents%20are%20supposed%20to%20follow%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20February%202023%20DHS%20policy%20governing%20use%20of%20force%20and%20the%202021%20ICE%20handbook%20direct%20agents%20to%20de-escalate%20situations%20when%20possible%20and%20give%20verbal%20warnings%20before%20using%20a%20deadly%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%202021%20handbook%20has%20different%20reporting%20requirements%20from%20ICE's%202004%20interim%20use-of-force%20policy.%20While%20the%20interim%20guidance%20instructed%20agents%20to%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%26quot%3B%20report%20an%20incident%20to%20their%20supervisor%2C%20the%20updated%20guidance%20says%20agents%20should%20report%20an%20incident%20within%20an%20hour%20only%20%26quot%3Bif%20it%20is%20safe%20and%20possible%20to%20do%20so%26quot%3B%3B%20otherwise%20they%20can%20do%20so%20%26quot%3Bas%20soon%20as%20is%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20handbooks%20require%20the%20agent's%20supervisor%20to%20follow%20up%20with%20a%20written%20report%20to%20ICE's%20Office%20of%20Professional%20Responsibility%3B%20the%202021%20handbook%20shortens%20that%20deadline%20from%20five%20days%20to%2048%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20these%20ICE%20and%20DHS%20policies%2C%20any%20use%20of%20force%20must%20be%20both%20%26quot%3Breasonable%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnecessary%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20when%20required%20for%20agents%20to%20protect%20themselves%20or%20to%20prevent%20the%20escape%20of%20a%20suspect%20who%20poses%20a%20serious%20danger%20to%20others.%20A%20DHS%202018%20policy%20provides%20even%20sharper%20guidance%20on%20the%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20%E2%80%94%20that%20officers%20must%20have%20a%20reasonable%20belief%20that%20they%20face%20imminent%20danger%20of%20serious%20bodily%20injury%20or%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20DHS%20policy%20says%20deadly%20force%20cannot%20be%20used%20against%20a%20person%20%26quot%3Bwhose%20actions%20are%20only%20a%20threat%20to%20themselves%20or%20property.%26quot%3B%20With%20limited%20exceptions%2C%20it%20also%20forbids%20agents%20from%20shooting%20a%20firearm%20from%20a%20moving%20vehicle%20or%20to%20disable%20a%20moving%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS%20policy%20now%20requires%20that%20officers%20be%20trained%20in%20the%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20at%20least%20annually%20and%20requires%20DHS%20agencies%2C%20including%20ICE%2C%20to%20ensure%20their%20officers%20are%20proficient%20in%20de-escalation%20tactics%20and%20techniques.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EICE's%202021%20handbook%20also%20prioritizes%20de-escalation.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20feasible%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3BAuthorized%20Officers%20shall%20employ%20tactics%20to%20de-escalate%2C%20i.e.%2C%20stabilize%2C%20slow%2C%20or%20reduce%20the%20intensity%20of%2C%20a%20potentially%20violent%20situation%20without%20using%20physical%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evening%20after%20the%20shooting%2C%20Martinez%20again%20got%20a%20call%20during%20her%20shift.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20was%20Soledad%2C%20Ramos's%20sister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoledad%20had%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20night%20calling%20hospitals%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20her%20brother.%20She%20finally%20found%20the%20local%20hospital%20where%20he'd%20been%20admitted%20and%20discovered%20he'd%20been%20transferred%20to%20another%20a%20half%20an%20hour%20away%2C%20where%20he%20was%20scheduled%20for%20surgery%20the%20next%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20day%2C%20Soledad%20went%20to%20bring%20Ramos%20home.%20She%20brought%20her%209-year-old%20son%20to%20the%20hospital%20with%20her%2C%20hoping%20that%20if%20ICE%20agents%20were%20there%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20arrest%20her%20with%20her%20young%20son.%20When%20she%20saw%20her%20brother%2C%20attached%20to%20tubes%20and%20wires%2C%20his%20arm%20bandaged%2C%20Soledad%20burst%20into%20tears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20found%20that%20the%20gunshot%20had%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20lacerated%26quot%3B%20his%20radial%20nerve%2C%20medical%20records%20show%2C%20requiring%20the%20administration%20of%20IV%20antibiotics.%20The%20surgeries%20would%20ultimately%20be%20extensive%2C%20involving%20a%20bone%20graft%2C%20the%20installation%20of%20a%20plate%2C%20and%20the%20removal%20of%20muscle%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20when%20we%20left%2C%20he%20was%20in%20a%20robe%20because%20we%20didn't%20know%20where%20his%20clothes%20were%2C%26quot%3B%20Soledad%20said.%20The%20bloody%20garments%20had%20likely%20been%20discarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20X-ray%20image%20of%20an%20arm%20showing%20a%20fragmented%20bone%20and%20bullet%20shrapnel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a143c3fb2b6bedb05a2c21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222015%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDoctors%20found%20that%20the%20ICE%20agent's%20gunshot%20had%20shattered%20a%20bone%20in%20Ramos%20Hernandez's%20arm%20and%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20lacerated%26quot%3B%20his%20radial%20nerve.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20women%20were%20not%20Ramos's%20first%20visitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20about%203%20a.m.%2C%20just%20six%20hours%20after%20the%20shooting%2C%20a%20Mississippi%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20officer%20named%20Leo%20Clemons%20arrived%20at%20the%20first%20hospital%20to%20interview%20Ramos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20had%20given%20him%20painkillers%2C%20but%20Ramos%20was%20still%20in%20immense%20pain.%20Clemons%20described%20his%20condition%20in%20an%20incident%20report%20as%20%26quot%3Bgroggy%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bwas%20able%20to%20speak%20enough%20broken%20English%20for%20us%20to%20have%20a%20conversation.%26quot%3B%20Ramos%20later%20told%20us%20that%20was%20not%20the%20case%3B%20he%20said%20he%20was%20so%20disoriented%20during%20the%20questioning%20by%20Clemons%20that%20he%20did%20not%20even%20remember%20meeting%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20practically%20unconscious%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2026-minute%20audio%20recording%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20Ramos%20moans%20frequently.%20He%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20understand%20all%20the%20questions.%20Clemons%20asks%20him%20to%20explain%20what%20happened%20and%20whether%20he%20could%20see%20the%20officer%20who%20shot%20him.%20%26quot%3BYou%20heard%20him%20but%20you%20couldn't%20see%20him%3F%26quot%3B%20Clemons%20asks.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know.%20I%20don't%20understand%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramos%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClemons%20did%20not%20request%20Spanish%20translation%20assistance%2C%20though%20it%20appears%20he%20knew%20he%20needed%20it%3B%20at%20one%20point%20he%20asks%20a%20nurse%20who%20comes%20to%20check%20on%20Ramos's%20vitals%20if%20she%20speaks%20Spanish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Ramos%20was%20interviewed%20within%20hours%20of%20being%20shot%2C%20the%20two%20Laurel%20police%20officers%20and%20one%20ICE%20officer%20at%20the%20scene%20waited%20a%20week%20to%20come%20into%20the%20station%20for%20questioning.%20Causey%2C%20the%20officer%20who%20shot%20Ramos%2C%20wasn't%20interviewed%20by%20MBI%20until%20two%20weeks%20later.%20MBI%20promised%20Ramos%20that%20an%20officer%20would%20interview%20him%20again%20after%20he%20got%20out%20of%20the%20hospital%2C%20but%20Ramos%20said%20no%20one%20ever%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Body%20cam%20footage%20of%20the%20police%20officer%20in%20a%20shooting%20scene.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a178be2d66759f66fe0e09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22542%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBody%20cam%20captures%20a%20Laurel%20police%20officer%20in%20the%20moments%20after%20Ramos%20was%20shot%20by%20an%20ICE%20agent.%3Cp%3ELaurel%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20MBI%20spokesperson%2C%20Bailey%20C.%20Martin%2C%20said%20Clemons%20was%20no%20longer%20with%20the%20bureau%20and%20he%20could%20not%20comment%20on%20%26quot%3Bdecisions%20made%20pertaining%20to%20a%20particular%20investigation.%26quot%3B%20Alvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20respond%20to%20detailed%20queries%20about%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20unusual%20that%20MBI%20was%20the%20agency%20that%20handled%20the%20Ramos%20shooting.%20But%20documents%20we%20obtained%20show%20that%20ICE%20assigned%20jurisdiction%20to%20another%20law-enforcement%20agency%20in%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20shootings%20by%20its%20agents%20that%20took%20place%20from%202015%20to%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20confirmed%20that%20ICE%20is%20required%20to%20notify%20local%20law%20enforcement%20of%20any%20allegations%20involving%20potentially%20criminal%20behavior%2C%20and%20that%20ICE%20and%20the%20DHS%20inspector%20general%20cooperate%20on%20any%20local%20law%20enforcement%20investigations.%20Yet%20we%20found%20that%20confusion%20over%20who%20had%20jurisdiction%20might%20have%20allowed%20some%20cases%20to%20escape%20criminal%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202019%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20deportation%20officer%20fired%20his%20weapon%20in%20Metairie%2C%20Louisiana.%20ICE%20said%20that%20while%20no%20one%20was%20struck%20or%20injured%2C%20the%20Jefferson%20Parish%20Sheriff's%20Office%20would%20investigate.%20But%20the%20sheriff's%20office%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wdsu.com%2Farticle%2Fshots-fired-during-ice-raid-in-metairie%2F29610529%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20local%20NBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20affiliate%20that%20it%20never%20opened%20an%20investigation.%20The%20Jefferson%20Parish%20Sheriff's%20Office%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20the%20fatal%20shooting%20of%20Mario%20Bass%20in%20Virginia%20was%20investigated%20either%2C%20once%20the%20Prince%20William%20County%20Commonwealth's%20Attorney's%20Office%20found%20it%20didn't%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20investigate.%20The%20office%20said%20it%20turned%20over%20all%20of%20its%20investigative%20files%20to%20the%20FBI%2C%20but%20the%20FBI%20press%20office%20said%20the%20bureau%20could%20neither%20confirm%20nor%20deny%20the%20existence%20of%20an%20investigation%20and%20declined%20to%20comment%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20identified%20several%20cases%20in%20which%20ICE%20agents%20may%20have%20hindered%20investigations%20by%20failing%20to%20follow%20protocol%20or%20provide%20documentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20case%20in%20Scottsdale%2C%20Arizona%2C%20in%20March%202018%2C%20a%20special%20agent%20with%20ICE's%20Homeland%20Security%20Investigations%20division%2C%20working%20in%20a%20team%20of%20three%2C%20fired%20at%20least%20three%20shots%20at%20a%20suspect%20who%20fell%20back%20onto%20the%20ground%20with%20a%20gun%20still%20in%20his%20hand.%20While%20writhing%20from%20his%20injuries%2C%20he%20pointed%20the%20weapon%20in%20the%20general%20direction%20of%20the%20special%20agent%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Scottsdale%20police%20report%20shared%20with%20us%20by%20Howard%20Center%20for%20Investigative%20Journalism%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University.%20The%20agent%20shot%20the%20man%20again%2C%20according%20to%20witnesses%20interviewed%20for%20the%20report%2C%20killing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Maricopa%20County%20District%20Attorney's%20Office%20investigated%20the%20incident%20and%20concluded%20that%20the%20HSI%20agent%20had%20disregarded%20the%20county's%20officer-involved%20shooting%20protocols%20by%20failing%20to%20remain%20on%20the%20scene%20and%20refusing%20to%20participate%20in%20interviews%20until%20six%20days%20later.%20The%20agent%20who%20repeatedly%20fired%20his%20weapon%20violated%20policy%20in%20four%20different%20ways%2C%20the%20investigators%20found%2C%20but%20was%20%26quot%3Bexcused%20by%20on%20scene%20Federal%20Homeland%20Policy%20Security%20Supervisors%20who%20relied%20on%20Internal%20Policies%20to%20justify%20the%20decisions%20made%20at%20the%20scene%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DA's%20report%20said.%20The%20DA's%20office%20said%20the%20violations%20could%20%26quot%3Bjustify%20further%20investigatory%20steps%26quot%3B%20but%20cleared%20the%20agent%20of%20wrongdoing%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20Mesa%2C%20Arizona%2C%20incident%20in%20May%202018%2C%20when%20three%20agents%20fired%2017%20shots%2C%20killing%20a%20suspect%2C%20the%20Maricopa%20County%20DA%20found%20that%20the%20agents%20violated%20protocol%20by%20failing%20to%20remain%20on%20the%20scene%20and%20delaying%20their%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20in%20this%20case%20for%20eight%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20June%202016%20incident%20in%20Chula%20Vista%2C%20California%2C%20an%20HSI%20agent%20named%20Chris%20Baroni%20advised%20a%20fellow%20HSI%20agent%2C%20Ronaldo%20Gonzalez%2C%20not%20to%20participate%20in%20an%20investigation.%20Gonzalez%20had%20just%20shot%20and%20killed%20someone%2C%20according%20to%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20body-wire%20recording%20obtained%20by%20the%20victim's%20family.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20worry%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Baroni%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BRemember%20...%20no%20statements%2C%20none%20of%20that%20shit.%26quot%3B%20(Attorneys%20representing%20Baroni%20and%20Gonzalez%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20their%20behalf.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJerry%20Robinette%2C%20who%20once%20oversaw%20Homeland%20Security%20Investigations%20operations%20as%20a%20special%20agent%20in%20charge%2C%20says%20the%20internal%20process%20for%20investigating%20ICE%20shootings%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bquagmire%26quot%3B%20littered%20with%20potential%20dead%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20agent%20must%20file%20a%20report%20for%20agency%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20an%20allegation%20of%20misconduct%2C%20DHS's%20Office%20of%20Inspector%20General%20has%20the%20right%20of%20first%20refusal%20to%20investigate.%20If%20the%20incident%20involves%20a%20shooting%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20inspector%20general%20gets%20involved%2C%20the%20case%20goes%20to%20ICE's%20Firearms%20and%20Use%20of%20Force%20Incident%20Review%20Committee.%20That%20committee%20determines%20whether%20the%20use%20of%20force%20violated%20ICE%20or%20DHS%20policies%20and%20whether%20the%20agency%20needs%20to%20respond%20by%20making%20changes%20to%20policy%2C%20tactics%2C%20or%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20incident%20involves%20potentially%20criminal%20behavior%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20inspector%20general%2C%20it%20will%20still%20get%20reviewed%20by%20ICE's%20Office%20of%20Professional%20Responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20either%20the%20inspector%20general%20or%20the%20review%20committee%20determines%20that%20a%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20violated%20policy%2C%20the%20case%20is%20referred%20to%20OPR%20for%20further%20investigation%2C%20according%20to%20Gretta%20Goodwin%2C%20a%20director%20on%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office's%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Justice%20team%20who%20has%20reviewed%20ICE's%20internal-investigation%20process.%20An%20officer's%20supervisor%20may%20also%20refer%20a%20case%20to%20the%20OPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20consistency%20with%20how%20some%20of%20those%20shootings%20have%20been%20handled%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robinette%2C%20who%20began%20his%20career%20as%20a%20US%20Customs%20special%20agent%20and%20ultimately%20managed%20a%20terrorist-financing%20task%20force%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20before%20retiring%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20process%20could%20fall%20apart%20at%20any%20point%20%E2%80%94%20a%20supervisor%20may%20choose%20not%20to%20escalate%20an%20incident%20for%20review%2C%20and%20the%20review%20committee%20may%20choose%20not%20to%20recommend%20discipline.%20Getting%20to%20the%20point%20of%20actual%20discipline%2C%20if%20it's%20imposed%20at%20all%2C%20can%20take%20years%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20inadequate%20recordkeeping%2C%20the%20GAO%20found%2C%20some%20use-of-force%20incidents%20might%20not%20be%20visible%20to%20DHS%20officials.%20And%20critically%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Professional%20Responsibility%20doesn't%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20issue%20disciplinary%20measures.%20OPR%20simply%20issues%20recommendations%20and%20%26quot%3Blocal%20management%20is%20responsible%20for%20taking%20any%20appropriate%20disciplinary%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20GAO%20report%20says%20such%20as%20a%20warning%20or%20a%20suspension.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Goodwin%20says%2C%20an%20agent's%20frontline%20supervisors%20ultimately%20decide%20whether%20the%20agent%20will%20face%20professional%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoodwin%20calls%20this%20a%20critical%20shortcoming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20board%20is%20saying%2C%20'This%20is%20a%20violation%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20ICE's%20use-of-force%20review%20committee.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20send%20it%20forward%20for%20disciplinary%20actions%2C%20and%20the%20manager%20decides%20not%20to%20discipline%2C%20it%20goes%20nowhere.%20That's%20it.%20So%20the%20individual%20who%20commits%20an%20egregious%20act%20doesn't%20get%20punished.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20those%20disciplinary%20recommendations%20are%20and%20whether%20they're%20implemented%20is%20never%20made%20public%2C%20even%20to%20oversight%20agencies.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20for%20us%20to%20get%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20what%20happens%20after%20the%20board%20finds%20you're%20out%20of%20compliance%2C%26quot%3B%20Goodwin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20Ramos%20case%20illustrates%20how%20ICE%20has%20never%20developed%20a%20robust%20system%20of%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Causey%20shot%20Ramos%2C%20it%20took%20almost%20a%20year%20for%20the%20case%20to%20be%20brought%20before%20a%20grand%20jury.%20MBI%20led%20the%20criminal%20investigation%2C%20which%20DHS%20%26quot%3Bmonitored%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20DHS's%20Office%20of%20the%20Inspector%20General.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ICE%20interim%20use-of-force%20policy%20that%20was%20in%20effect%20at%20the%20time%20outlines%20a%20range%20of%20documentation%20the%20agency%20is%20required%20to%20collect%20when%20an%20agent%20uses%20deadly%20force%2C%20including%20witness%20and%20officer%20statements%2C%20medical%20reports%2C%20and%20photos%20and%20diagrams%20of%20the%20scene.%20But%20the%20inspector%20general's%20report%20made%20reference%20only%20to%20police%20statements%20and%20body-camera%20footage%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20other%20documents%20may%20not%20have%20been%20collected%20or%20turned%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22878%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20list%20of%20items%20under%20the%20heading%20Appendix%202%20Shooting%20or%20Use%20of%20Deadly%20Force%20Incident%20Investigation%20reports%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a141762d66759f66fde082%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EICE%20requires%20a%20robust%20list%20of%20records%20to%20be%20compiled%20when%20agents%20fire%20their%20weapons.%20But%20an%20inspector%20general%20found%20that%20few%20of%20these%20documents%20were%20collected%20in%20the%20Ramos%20case.%3Cp%3EImmigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETommy%20Cox%2C%20Laurel's%20police%20chief%2C%20told%20us%20that%20he%20was%20unable%20to%20recall%20whether%20ICE%20or%20MBI%20ever%20reached%20out%20to%20interview%20the%20officers%20present%20the%20night%20of%20the%20shooting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inspector%20general%20found%20that%20ICE%20didn't%20follow%20its%20own%20protocols%20in%20another%20way.%20The%20policy%20said%20any%20agent%20who%20uses%20deadly%20force%20that%20results%20in%20death%20or%20serious%20injury%20shall%20be%20placed%20on%20leave%20for%20three%20consecutive%20workdays.%20In%20Causey's%20case%2C%20he%20took%20time%20on%20his%20own%20accord%20and%20returned%20to%20work%20before%20the%20grand%20jury%20made%20a%20decision%20in%20the%20case%2C%20nearly%20a%20year%20after%20the%20shooting%2C%20not%20to%20indict%20him.%20He%20was%20never%20suspended%2C%20and%20the%20OIG%20report%20says%20there%20is%20no%20record%20of%20either%20his%20absence%20or%20his%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20person%20whose%20name%20was%20redacted%2C%20presumably%20Causey's%20supervisor%2C%20told%20the%20inspector%20general's%20office%20that%20since%20the%20language%20in%20the%20policy%20says%20%26quot%3Bshall%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20didn't%20believe%20a%20leave%20of%20absence%20was%20%26quot%3Bmandatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Office%20of%20the%20Inspector%20General%20said%20it%20was%20unable%20to%20interview%20Causey%2C%20an%20Army%20reservist%2C%20because%20he%20was%20on%20active%20duty%20in%20Africa.%20The%20investigation%20closed%2C%20and%20the%20inspector%20general's%20report%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20ICE%20and%20DHS%20have%20repeatedly%20come%20under%20scrutiny%20for%20inadequate%20procedures%20to%20address%20employee%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20as%20ICE%20was%20enforcing%20Donald%20Trump's%20anti-immigration%20policies%2C%20the%20DHS%20inspector%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oig.dhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fassets%2F2017%2FOIG-17-22-Jan17.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20department%20lacked%20%26quot%3Bpolicies%20that%20emphasize%20the%20respect%20for%20human%20life%20when%20using%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20OIG%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oig.dhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fassets%2F2019-06%2FOIG-19-48-Jun19.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20DHS%20was%20not%20adequately%20handling%20misconduct%20allegations%20because%20its%20policy%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20include%20procedures%20for%20reporting%20allegations%20of%20misconduct%2C%20clear%20and%20specific%20supervisor%20roles%20and%20expectations%2C%20or%20clearly%20defined%20key%20discipline%20terms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20department-wide%20procedures%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDHS%20cannot%20ensure%20supervisors%20administer%20disciplinary%20actions%20consistently%20and%20may%20leave%20itself%20vulnerable%20to%20costly%20litigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS%20concurred%20with%20the%20report's%20recommendations%2C%20and%20subsequent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Ffiles.cnas.org%2Fdocuments%2FCNAS-Report-HomelandSecurity-final-updated-060820-web-2.pdf%3Fmtime%3D20200609093103%26focal%3Dnone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20think%20tanks%20and%20human-rights%20organizations%20have%20come%20to%20similar%20conclusions.%20Yet%20DHS's%20new%20use-of-force%20policy%2C%20released%20in%20February%202023%2C%20does%20little%20to%20strengthen%20these%20shortcomings%20in%20oversight%20beyond%20establishing%20new%20data%20collection%20and%20reporting%20mechanisms%2C%20such%20as%20requiring%20that%20DHS%20agencies%20participate%20in%20the%20FBI's%20Use%20of%20Force%20Data%20Collection%20Program.%20It%20bars%20some%20dangerous%20practices%20%E2%80%94%20critically%2C%20it%20prohibits%20shooting%20at%20a%20moving%20vehicle%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20does%20not%20provide%20remedies%20for%20people%20harmed%20by%20such%20practices%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202020%20report%20from%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20found%20%26quot%3Bfragmented%20oversight%26quot%3B%20at%20DHS%3B%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20the%20DHS%20inspector%20general%20told%20Congress%20that%20the%20agency%20was%20%26quot%3Bstruggling%20to%20mature%20as%20an%20organization%26quot%3B%20and%20suffered%20a%20%26quot%3Bdysfunctional%20work%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20administration%20has%20been%20committed%20to%20reining%20in%20their%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jennifer%20Chac%C3%B3n%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20immigration%2C%20constitutional%2C%20and%20criminal%20law%20at%20Stanford%20Law%20School.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20accountability%20for%20agents%2C%20you%20don't%20see%20a%20lot%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarc%C3%ADa%20Ramos%2C%20the%20professor%20at%20Ohio%20State%20Law%2C%20says%20ICE's%20aggressive%20policies%20enacted%20under%20Trump%20remain%20today.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20they%20weren't%20created%20under%20Biden%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20taken%20ownership%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20want%20DHS%20leaders%20and%20the%20White%20House%20to%20take%20seriously%20that%20the%20largest%20armed%20law-enforcement%20agency%20in%20the%20country%20are%20constantly%20interacting%20with%20ordinary%20people%20and%20those%20people%20have%20a%20lot%20at%20stake%20and%20should%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20what%20to%20expect%20of%20those%20armed%20law-enforcement%20officers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20July%2C%20the%20GAO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fgao-23-105927.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20that%20DHS%20had%20undercounted%20use-of-force%3C%2Fa%3E%20incidents%20across%20agencies%20and%20had%20never%20set%20up%20a%20plan%20to%20analyze%20use-of-force%20data.%20Even%20when%20DHS%20agencies%20did%20submit%20data%2C%20the%20report%20found%2C%20they%20sometimes%20recorded%20multiple%20uses%20of%20force%20as%20a%20single%20incident%20or%20in%20a%20single%20report%2C%20which%20not%20only%20disguised%20the%20true%20tally%20but%20lost%20track%20of%20incidents%20that%20could%20have%20informed%20policy%20or%20training%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GAO%20report%2C%20which%20Goodwin%20authored%2C%20said%20it%20had%20previously%20recommended%20that%20two%20federal%20agencies%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20and%20ICE%2C%20issue%20updated%20data-collection%20policies.%20The%20Secret%20Service%20complied%20in%20February%202023%2C%20but%20ICE%20still%20has%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20GAO%20was%20preparing%20its%20report%2C%20ICE%20reported%20that%20it%20had%20implemented%20a%20couple%20of%20changes%20to%20its%20policies%20and%20training%20curriculum.%20But%20Goodwin%20said%20ICE%20didn't%20provide%20any%20substantiation%20that%20those%20changes%20had%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20complying%20with%20Biden's%20May%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2022%2F05%2F31%2F2022-11810%2Fadvancing-effective-accountable-policing-and-criminal-justice-practices-to-enhance-public-trust-and%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecutive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20DHS%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20required%20its%20member%20agencies%20to%20report%20use-of-force%20data%20%E2%80%94%20but%20asked%20for%20data%20going%20back%20only%20to%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20after%20he%20was%20shot%2C%20Ramos%20hired%20an%20attorney%2C%20Timothy%20Cerniglia%2C%20who%20has%20since%20brought%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20Causey.%20In%20preparing%20for%20the%20suit%2C%20Cerniglia%20was%20stymied%20by%20ICE's%20opacity.%20In%20response%20to%20a%20Freedom%20of%20Information%20Act%20request%2C%20the%20agency%20refused%20to%20give%20him%20the%20use-of-force%20incident%20report%2C%20citing%20a%20state%20exemption%20for%20law-enforcement%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20February%2C%20a%20judge%20had%20dismissed%20all%20the%20claims%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20prove%20that%20the%20agents%20had%20violated%20his%20constitutional%20rights.%20In%20April%2C%20Cerniglia%20filed%20an%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-chart-id%3D%5C%22lawsuits%5C%22%20data-chart-theme%3D%5C%22bi%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BPrivate%20lawsuits%20are%20basically%20the%20only%20option%20and%20they're%20not%20a%20particularly%20great%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Garc%C3%ADa%20Ramos%2C%20the%20Ohio%20State%20Law%20professor.%20%26quot%3BBut%20really%20they're%20the%20only%20genuine%20mechanism%20for%20someone%20who%20is%20aggrieved%20because%20of%20an%20ICE%20agent's%20use%20of%20force%20to%20be%20heard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartinez%2C%20Ramos's%20partner%2C%20said%20her%20life%20has%20two%20eras%3A%20before%20and%20after%20the%20shooting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Ramos%20came%20home%20from%20the%20hospital%2C%20she%20was%20the%20one%20who%20helped%20him%20shower%2C%20fed%20him%2C%20and%20organized%20his%20medication.%20She%20also%20took%20over%20financial%20responsibilities%20for%20the%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamos's%20recovery%20has%20been%20slow.%20He%20spent%20nearly%20two%20years%20in%20the%20bedroom%20the%20couple%20shared%2C%20where%20the%20window%20looks%20out%20onto%20the%20street%20where%20he%20was%20shot.%20Martinez%20says%20he%20still%20sometimes%20experiences%20a%20dread%20so%20severe%20he%20does%20not%20leave%20his%20bedroom%20all%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20left%20him%20feeling%20really%20depressed%20and%20with%20no%20sort%20of%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20Soledad%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20suffering%20every%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%20white%20home%20on%20a%20rural%20road%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a1499980d4d5da13d6d62d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222403%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERamos%20and%20Hernandez's%20home%20in%20Laurel%2C%20Mississippi.%3Cp%3ETimothy%20Ivy%20for%20The%20Trace%20and%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20years%20later%2C%20he%20still%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20%245%2C000%20he%20owes%20for%20the%20surgeries%20he%20received%20to%20treat%20the%20gunshot%20wound%20and%20later%20to%20graft%20and%20replace%20damaged%20bone.%20He%20hasn't%20regained%20full%20mobility%20in%20his%20arm.%20And%20he%20never%20returned%20to%20the%20poultry%20plant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20she%20needed%20to%20be%20home%20more%20and%20couldn't%20work%20late%20hours%2C%20Martinez%20had%20to%20quit%20her%20job%20at%20the%20poultry%20plant%2C%20too.%20To%20maintain%20a%20flexible%20schedule%2C%20she%20turned%20to%20cleaning%20homes%20and%20selling%20street%20food.%20The%20pay%20was%20less%2C%20and%20more%20sporadic%2C%20and%20yet%20her%20earnings%20had%20to%20support%20them%20both.%20Soon%2C%20Martinez%20also%20stopped%20sending%20money%20back%20home%20to%20her%20family%20in%20Oaxaca%20%E2%80%94%20her%20two%20daughters%20and%20her%2093-year-old%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%20after%20the%20shooting%2C%20Ramos's%20main%20form%20of%20income%20was%20working%20the%20blueberry%20harvest.%20But%20the%20picking%20season%20is%20very%20short%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%20three%20months%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20came%20to%20work%2C%20and%20now%20I%20can't%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDriskell%2C%20the%20Laurel%20police%20officer%20who%20pulled%20them%20over%20that%20night%2C%20never%20indicated%20to%20Ramos%20that%20he%20was%20getting%20a%20traffic%20ticket%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%20But%20Driskell%20wrote%20up%20two%20while%20Ramos%20was%20in%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%20holds%20out%20his%20scarred%20arm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a14a6bfb2b6bedb05a30f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222403%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERamos%20underwent%20multiple%20surgeries%20after%20he%20was%20shot.%20He%20never%20regained%20full%20mobility%20in%20his%20arm.%3Cp%3ETimothy%20Ivy%20for%20The%20Trace%20and%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERamos%20and%20Martinez%20had%20been%20thinking%20about%20going%20back%20to%20Mexico%20anyway.%20%3Cem%3EWhat's%20the%20benefit%20of%20being%20here%20any%20longer%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethey%20asked%20each%20other.%20He's%20been%20worried%20his%20aging%20mother%20might%20die%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Soledad%20insisted%20that%20Ramos%20stay%20through%20to%20the%20end%20of%20his%20appeal.%20He%20may%20have%20been%20an%20unauthorized%20immigrant%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20deserve%20to%20be%20shot%20in%20the%20act%20of%20surrendering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20the%20sense%20that%20they%20have%20the%20right%20to%20use%20guns%20and%20that%20they%20will%20be%20protected%2C%26quot%3B%20Soledad%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20had%20no%20gun.%20He%20had%20nothing%20on%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20May%2C%20Ramos%20had%20another%20encounter%20with%20the%20Laurel%20police%20in%20which%20ICE%20got%20involved.%20He%20was%20pulled%20over%20for%20a%20suspected%20DUI%2C%20and%20this%20time%20the%20police%20said%20they%20found%20drugs%20in%20the%20car.%20Ramos%20denies%20that%20the%20drugs%20were%20his%2C%20but%20he%20hasn't%20yet%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20enter%20a%20not-guilty%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2030%2C%20he%20was%20brought%20from%20the%20Laurel%20jail%20into%20ICE%20detention%2C%20where%20he%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20grant%20from%20the%20Fund%20for%20Investigative%20Journalism%20supported%20research%20for%20this%20story.%20Loevy%20%26amp%3B%20Loevy%20provided%20pro%20bono%20legal%20support%20in%20a%20public-records%20suit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECredits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReporting%3A%20Lila%20Hassan%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEditing%3A%20Aviva%20Shen%2C%20Tali%20Woodward%2C%20Esther%20Kaplan%2C%20John%20Cook%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%3A%20Paco%20Alvarez%2C%20Emma%20Davis%2C%20Rosemarie%20Ho%2C%20Schuyler%20Mitchell%2C%20Iqra%20Salah%2C%20Nina%20Zweig%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhotography%3A%20Tim%20Ivy%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20visualization%3A%20Daniel%20Nass%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDesign%20and%20visuals%3A%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2C%20Selin%20Thomas%2C%20Isabel%20Fernandez-Pujol%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbimedia.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbistudios%2F_00%2Fdev_edit%2Fgraphics%2F2024%2F07%2F2024-07-ice-embeds%2Findex.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%