A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225211%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20a%20basketball.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa6d7a1a227600e6332813%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222606%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20thing%20about%20sports%20betting%20is%20addicts%20think%20their%20problem%20is%20the%20solution.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-betting-apps-online-gambling-lottery-draftkings-fanduel-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESports%20betting%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20fun.%20It's%20neat%20to%20place%20a%20couple%20of%20bets%20on%20your%20phone%2C%20kick%20back%2C%20and%20watch%20the%20game.%20It%20adds%20an%20extra%20edge%20to%20an%20experience%20you%20likely%20already%20enjoy%2C%20and%2C%20hey%2C%20if%20that%20makes%20the%20whole%20thing%20a%20little%20more%20entertaining%2C%20good%20for%20you.%20But%20that's%20not%20what%20everyone%20who%20gambles%20on%20sports%20is%20doing.%20A%20small%20but%20not%20insignificant%20amount%20of%20the%20population%20is%20in%20over%20their%20heads%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20getting%20increasingly%20scary.%20They're%20winding%20up%20in%20the%20laps%20of%20debt%20collectors%2C%20missing%20car%20payments%2C%20and%2C%20in%20dire%20cases%2C%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Ftypes-of-bankruptcies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20bankrupt%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4903302%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20takes%20a%20look%20at%20what's%20happened%20to%20consumer%20financial%20health%20in%20the%2038%20states%20that%20have%20greenlighted%20sports%20betting%20since%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%20struck%20down%20a%20federal%20law%20prohibiting%20it.%20The%20findings%20are%2C%20well%2C%20rough.%20The%20researchers%20found%20that%20the%20average%20credit%20score%20in%20states%20that%20legalized%20any%20form%20of%20sports%20gambling%20decreased%20by%200.3%25%20after%20about%20four%20years%20and%20that%20the%20negative%20impact%20was%20stronger%20where%20online%20sports%20gambling%20is%20allowed%2C%20with%20credit%20scores%20dipping%20in%20those%20areas%20by%201%25.%20They%20also%20found%20an%208%25%20increase%20in%20debt-collection%20amounts%20and%20a%2028%25%20increase%20in%20bankruptcies%20where%20online%20sports%20betting%20was%20given%20the%20go-ahead.%20By%20their%20estimation%2C%20that%20translates%20to%20about%20100%2C000%20extra%20bankruptcies%20each%20year%20in%20the%20states%20that%20have%20legalized%20sports%20betting.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20who%20fell%20dangerously%20behind%20on%20their%20car%20loans%20went%20up%2C%20too.%20Oddly%20enough%2C%20credit-card%20delinquencies%20fell%2C%20but%20the%20researchers%20believe%20that's%20because%20banks%20wind%20up%20lowering%20credit%20limits%20to%20try%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20risky%20consumer%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20look%20at%20the%20general%20introduction%20of%20sports%20gambling%20and%20separately%20the%20introduction%20of%20online%20access%2C%20which%20is%20mostly%20these%20mobile%20apps%20like%20DraftKings%20and%20FanDuel%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brett%20Hollenbeck%2C%20an%20associate%20marketing%20professor%20at%20UCLA's%20Anderson%20School%20of%20Management%20and%20one%20of%20the%20paper's%20authors.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20we%20find%20the%20big%20effects%20is%20when%20the%20online%20mobile%20access%20goes%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20tracks%3A%20The%20closer%20you%20live%20to%20a%20casino%2C%20the%20likelier%20you%20are%20to%20develop%20a%20gambling%20problem.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-sports-betting-fantasy-games-taking-over-college-campuses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproliferation%20of%20sports-betting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20the%20casino%20now%20lives%20in%20people's%20pockets.%20The%20addictive%20nature%20of%20a%20slot%20machine%2C%20with%20that%20rush%20of%20pulling%20the%20lever%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20faster%20and%20faster%2C%20is%20now%20in%20a%20hyperaccessible%20format%20from%20the%20couch.%20When%20the%20researchers%20broke%20it%20down%2C%20they%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgambling-young-men-sports-betting-crypto-meme-stock-market-addiction-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20were%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20looks%20like%20the%20problems%20are%20biggest%20for%20younger%20men%20and%20especially%20younger%20men%20in%20low-income%20counties%2C%26quot%3B%20Hollenbeck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense%20that%20the%20explosion%20of%20legal%20sports%20gambling%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20on%20which%20Americans%20spent%20%24119.84%20billion%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20might%20be%20accompanied%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20problem%20gambling.%20The%20greater%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20get%20exposure%20to%20any%20form%20of%20potentially%20addictive%20behavior%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20number%20who%20could%20be%20vulnerable.%20About%201%25%20of%20US%20adults%20have%20a%20severe%20gambling%20problem%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Council%20on%20Problem%20Gambling%2C%20and%202%25%20to%203%25%20have%20a%20mild%20or%20moderate%20problem.%20That%20amounts%2C%20in%20total%2C%20to%20somewhere%20between%207.5%20million%20and%2010.5%20million%20people.%20In%20states%20across%20the%20country%20that%20have%20legalized%20sports%20betting%2C%20calls%20to%20addiction%20hotlines%20have%20been%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProblem%20gambling%20can%20have%20several%20negative%20consequences%2C%20financial%20and%20otherwise.%20It%20affects%20people's%20relationships%2C%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%20their%20bank%20accounts.%20If%20it%20gets%20severe%20enough%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20legal%20harm%2C%20too.%20Studies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10098700%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20found%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%2027%25%20to%2060%25%20of%20people%20with%20a%20gambling%20disorder%20have%20engaged%20in%20a%20related%20illegal%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tricky%20thing%20about%20gambling%20addiction%20is%20that%20people%20see%20their%20problem%20as%20their%20solution.%20The%20habit%20gets%20someone%20into%20a%20hole%2C%20and%20instead%20of%20deciding%20to%20stop%20gambling%20and%20try%20to%20slowly%20pay%20down%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Faverage-american-debt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20will%20keep%20at%20it%2C%20believing%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Enext%20big%20win%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewill%20get%20them%20out%20of%20the%20red%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20allow%20them%20to%20stop.%20But%20that's%20not%20how%20it%20works%20%E2%80%94%20continuing%20to%20gamble%20makes%20the%20hole%20they're%20in%20even%20deeper%2C%20and%20even%20if%20they%20do%20win%2C%20they%20can't%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20never%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michelle%20Malkin%2C%20the%20director%20of%20East%20Carolina%20University's%20Gambling%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Policy%20Initiative.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20keep%20on%20gambling.%20So%20it's%20this%20cyclical%20thought%20pattern%20of%2C%20'I%20can%20fix%20my%20problems%20by%20keeping%20gambling%20and%20getting%20that%20next%20win.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20can%20fall%20victim%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-gamblers-fallacy-and-the-hot-hand-2014-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egambler's%20fallacy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20they%20think%20past%20events%20make%20future%20events%20more%20or%20less%20likely%20even%20though%20they're%20completely%20disconnected.%20Say%20a%20bettor%20is%20on%20a%20losing%20streak%2C%20so%20they%20feel%20like%20that%20makes%20it%20more%20probable%20their%20next%20bet%20will%20hit%2C%20even%20though%20the%20odds%20haven't%20changed%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGambling%20money%20that%20used%20to%20just%20come%20from%20the%20entertainment%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20pile%20of%20cash%20that's%20spent%20on%20movie%20tickets%20or%20a%20restaurant%20%E2%80%94%20starts%20to%20come%20from%20other%2C%20nondiscretionary%20budgets%20to%20fund%20someone's%20problem%20gambling%20habit.%20Suddenly%2C%20people%20find%20themselves%20wagering%20money%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20go%20to%20their%20rent%20or%20mortgage%20or%20car%20payment%20or%20tuition.%20And%20it%20just%20snowballs%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20everyone%20gets%20all%20excited%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20really%20large%20credit-card%20debt%2C%20really%20large%20debts%20to%20friends%20and%20family.%20I'll%20give%20you%20five%20grand%20here%2C%20or%2010%20grand%2C%20whatever.%20A%20lot%20of%20online%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Timothy%20Fong%2C%20a%20clinical%20professor%20of%20psychiatry%20at%20UCLA%20and%20a%20codirector%20of%20its%20gambling-studies%20program.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20debt%20you%20can%20easily%20repay%20because%20it's%20a%20large%20sum.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20recently%20met%20with%20a%20patient%20%E2%80%94%20a%20man%20in%20his%20mid-20s%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20making%20somewhere%20between%20%2440%2C000%20and%20%2450%2C000%20a%20year%20and%20had%20accumulated%20over%20%24300%2C000%20in%20gambling%20debts.%20The%20desire%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20that%20debt%20is%20now%20driving%20his%20gambling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20debt%20was%20really%20shameful%2C%26quot%3B%20Fong%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wanted%20to%20hide%20it.%20He%20didn't%20like%20it.%20It%20was%20a%20reminder%20that%20he%20was%20a%20quote-unquote%20loser.%20It's%20really%20emotional%20debt%20that%20really%20sucks%2C%20for%20lack%20of%20a%20better%20word.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20that%20fuels%20sports-betting%20apps%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%2C%20where%20legal%2C%20iGaming%2C%20like%20online%20slot%20machines%20and%20blackjack%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20the%20only%20innovation%20exacerbating%20people's%20addictions%20and%20accompanying%20debt%2C%20Fong%20added.%20The%20tech%20that's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loans%2Fcash-advance-vs-payday-loan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20it%20easier%20and%20faster%20to%20get%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20factor%2C%20too.%20He%20sees%20clients%20who%20are%20able%20to%20get%20hundreds%20and%20even%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20from%20online%20lenders%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes%20to%20fuel%20their%20habits.%20Bettors%20get%20cash%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20with%20no%20collateral%2C%20no%20credit%20score%2C%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20so%20they%20can%20continue%20to%20gamble%20it%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20men's%20finances%20appear%20to%20be%20most%20at%20risk%20in%20the%20proliferation%20of%20sports%20betting%20in%20America.%20A%202023%20study%20on%20the%20prevalence%20of%20gambling%20in%20New%20Jersey%20found%20that%20men%20had%20double%20the%20rate%20of%20high-risk%20problem%20gambling%20than%20women%20and%20that%20those%20ages%2018%20to%2044%20were%20at%20the%20highest%20risk.%20In%20the%20sports%20world%2C%20we've%20recently%20seen%20some%20high-profile%20examples%20of%20young%20men%20getting%20into%20hot%20water%20from%20sports%20betting.%20The%20MLB%20player%20Shohei%20Ohtani's%20former%20interpreter%20Ippei%20Mizuhara%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshohei-ohtani-interpreter-ippei-mizuhara-charged-sports-betting-court-documents-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epleaded%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%20to%20taking%20almost%20%2417%20million%20from%20the%20baseball%20star%20to%20pay%20off%20gambling%20debts.%20The%20NBA%20player%20Jontay%20Porter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnba-ban-jontay-porter-toronto-raptors-easy-call-why-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20barred%20from%20the%20league%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20betting%20on%20basketball%20games%20and%20has%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20federal%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20wire%20fraud%20after%20agreeing%20with%20other%20gamblers%20to%20withdraw%20himself%20from%20games.%20He%20said%20he%20did%20it%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20out%20from%20under%20large%20gambling%20debts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMen%20are%20socialized%20into%20gambling%20and%20sports%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20Malkin%20said%2C%20which%20means%20they'll%20bet%20on%20sports%20more%20than%20women%20earlier.%20However%2C%20she%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20bet%20on%20sports%20even%20when%20it's%20illegal%2C%20which%20isn't%20true%20for%20women%2C%20who%20have%20been%20likelier%20to%20get%20in%20on%20the%20game%20once%20states%20legalize%20sports%20gambling.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20women%20aren't%20immune%20to%20gambling%20addiction%20or%20related%20debt.%20Still%2C%20as%20it%20stands%2C%20it's%20men%20who%20are%20getting%20into%20trouble%20at%20higher%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGambling%20disorder%20is%20anywhere%20between%201%25%20to%208%25%2C%20depending%20on%20what%20state%2C%20what%20jurisdiction%2C%20and%20what%20community%20you're%20looking%20at%2C%20and%20for%20young%20people%2C%20it's%20much%20higher%2C%20especially%20for%20young%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20Malkin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20legal%20sports%20gambling%20has%20become%20normalized%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20it's%20still%20pretty%20new%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20we're%20learning%20about%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20fly.%20What%20does%20it%20mean%20for%20addiction%3F%20For%20finances%3F%20Even%20for%20the%20benefits%20lawmakers%20and%20lobbyists%20promised%20when%20pushing%20legalization%20through%3F%20We're%20still%20getting%20answers.%20For%20most%20people%2C%20gambling%20doesn't%20become%20a%20problem%2C%20and%20if%20it%20does%2C%20it%20doesn't%20happen%20overnight.%20Disordered%20gambling%20can%20take%20months%20and%20even%20years%20to%20set%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20not%20clear%20whether%20some%20of%20the%20trade-offs%20states%20have%20made%20in%20rubber-stamping%20sports%20betting%20are%20worthwhile.%20Yes%2C%20it's%20generating%20revenue%2C%20but%20reasonable%20minds%20can%20disagree%20about%20whether%20that%20revenue%20is%20worth%20it%2C%20given%20the%20risks.%20Sports-betting%20revenue%20being%20used%20for%20gambling-addiction%20programs%20is%20probably%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20little%20strange.%20Legal%20sports%20betting%20is%20better%20than%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20the%20shadows%2C%20but%20it%20also%20means%20more%20people%20are%20betting%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20bad%20thing%20that%20we%20have%20legalization%2C%26quot%3B%20Malkin%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20bad%20is%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20states%20and%20the%20federal%20government%20taking%20the%20responsibility%20piece%20of%20that%2C%20at%20least%20not%20universally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESportsbooks%20have%20mechanisms%20in%20place%20to%20try%20to%20keep%20gamblers%20from%20going%20off%20the%20rails%2C%20including%20cooling-off%20periods%20and%20features%20that%20let%20bettors%20set%20limits%20on%20their%20deposits%20and%20wagers.%20But%2C%20of%20course%2C%20their%20business%20model%20is%20not%20to%20stop%20people%20from%20gambling%2