on%20world%20where%20I%20could%20choose%20between%20dozens%20of%20websites%20made%20for%20kids%20my%20age.%20At%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclub-penguin-died-disney-and-money-destroyed-a-community-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClub%20Penguin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20adopted%20colorful%20pets%20called%20puffles%20and%20purchased%20kitsch%20furniture%20for%20my%20virtual%20igloo.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchrissy-teigen-neopets-fan-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeopets%3C%2Fa%3E%20haven%20of%20Neopia%2C%20I%20visited%20the%20money%20tree%20to%20collect%20items%20others%20had%20discarded.%20On%20Pony%20Island%2C%20I%20dressed%20up%20my%20herd%20of%20colorful%20horses%20(despite%20my%20aversion%20to%20the%20animal%2C%20I%20found%20the%20game%20irresistibly%20cool).%20And%20on%20Furry%20Paws%2C%20my%20favorite%20game%20of%20all%2C%20I%20raised%2C%20trained%2C%20and%20bred%20virtual%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20game%20so%20much%20that%20I%20taught%20myself%20HTML%20and%20CSS%20to%20decorate%20my%20kennel%20above%20and%20beyond%20the%20in-game%20options.%20I%20designed%20quirky%2C%20unreadable%20fonts%20and%20banners%20that%20flashed%20so%20brightly%20they%20should%20have%20come%20with%20a%20warning%20sign.%20Nearly%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20I%20took%20those%20skills%20to%20the%20next%20level%20by%20studying%20computer%20science%20in%20college.%20I%20can't%20help%20but%20think%20my%20afternoons%20on%20Furry%20Paws%20shaped%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20at%2028%2C%20I%20stick%20to%20just%20a%20few%2C%20far%20less%20joyful%20websites.%20I%20read%20the%20news%20or%20scroll%20through%20Instagram%20and%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20my%20colorful%20cartoon%20pets%20long%20ago%20abandoned.%20Even%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20back%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fredownloading-club-penguin-made-me-feel-better-power-of-nostalgia-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelive%20the%20nostalgia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20couldn't.%20Most%20of%20my%20online%20childhood%20haunts%20don't%20exist%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%2C%20not%20in%20the%20way%20that%20I%20remember%20them.%20It's%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20when%20childhood%20memorabilia%20of%20generations%20past%20like%20comic%20books%2C%20board%20games%2C%20and%20cartoons%20stuck%20around%20for%20decades.%20As%20younger%20generations%20spend%20more%20and%20more%20of%20their%20lives%20on%20the%20internet%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneal-agarwal-saves-internet-making-web-fun-again-games-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20ephemeral%20than%20most%20realize%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20as%20internet%20trends%20cycle%20through%20increasingly%20brief%20lifespans%2C%20our%20past%20disappears%20earlier%20and%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20late%202000s%20and%20early%202010s%20were%20the%20heyday%20of%20massive%20multiplayer%20online%20games%20designed%20for%20young%20kids.%20Dozens%20of%20games%20emerged%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2007%2F12%2Fgreedy-webkins-infuriates-parents-bombards-kids-with-ads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWebkinz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20real%20stuffed%20animals%20morphed%20into%20digital%20pets%3B%20Toontown%2C%20Disney's%20cartoon%20universe%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoshi-monsters-kids-fad-2011-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMoshi%20Monsters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%2080%20million%20players%20worldwide%20raised%20pet%20monsters%3B%20and%20Stardoll%2C%20a%20dress-up%20game%20that%20at%20one%20point%20had%20400%20million%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20generation%20of%20young%20millennials%20and%20elder%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20these%20games%20were%20far%20more%20than%20just%20a%20way%20to%20pass%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20formative%20experiences.%20Dylan%20Maleno%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20from%20Pennsylvania%2C%20recalled%20starting%20his%20online%20gaming%20journey%20at%20just%205%20or%206.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20big%20on%20Club%20Penguin%2C%20Wizard101%2C%20Moshi%20Monsters%2C%20and%20this%20obscure%20one%20called%20Ourworld%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20He%20was%20particularly%20drawn%20to%20their%20cozy%20environments%20and%20their%20%26quot%3Bsense%20of%20false%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%20Most%20games%20involved%20furnishing%20virtual%20homes%2C%20decorating%20spaces%2C%20and%20caring%20for%20digital%20pets%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%2C%20an%20online%20version%20of%20playing%20house.%20%26quot%3BIt%20probably%20tickles%20some%20part%20of%20the%20undeveloped%20brain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclub-penguin-shutting-down-mourning-2017-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClub%20Penguin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20ran%20from%202005%20to%202017%2C%20stands%20out%20as%20one%20of%20the%20era's%20most%20beloved%20virtual%20worlds.%20At%20its%20peak%2C%20it%20had%20more%20than%20200%20million%20users.%20Lance%20Priebe%2C%20who%20created%20Club%20Penguin%20and%20sold%20it%20to%20Disney%20in%202007%2C%20said%20that%20the%20game%20was%20%26quot%3Bmodeled%20like%20a%20Saturday%20morning%20cartoon%20or%20a%20show%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bcultural%20artifact.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20child%2C%20I'd%20rush%20home%20from%20school%20to%20watch%20cartoons%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20same%20generation%20logged%20into%20Club%20Penguin%20to%20play%20with%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJake%20Hahn%2C%20a%20Gen%20Zer%20in%20Illinois%2C%20perfectly%20captures%20the%20impact%20the%20game%20had%20in%20%26quot%3BClub%20Penguin%20Is%20Gone%20and%20I%20Am%20Still%20Not%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsouthblueprint.com%2F26906%2Fopinions%2Fclub-penguin-is-gone-and-i-am-still-not-okay%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20wrote%20for%20his%20high-school%20newspaper%20in%202021.%20Reflecting%20on%20his%20experiences%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20memorized%20everyone's%20online%20flightless%20bird%20more%20than%20any%20math%20problem%20I've%20ever%20worked%20on.%20Those%20chance%20meetings%20on%20the%20virtual%20island%20were%20all%20we%20talked%20about%20for%20days%20afterward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20networking%20aspect%20of%20the%20games%20was%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20appeal.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20exciting%20to%20have%20those%20interactions.%20Even%20if%20they're%20not%20always%20super%20positive%2C%26quot%3B%20Sara%20Grimes%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto's%20Faculty%20of%20Information%20who%20specializes%20in%20children's%20digital-media%20culture%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20experiment%20with%20different%20facets%20of%20the%20self%20and%20not%20be%20beholden%20to%20the%20realities%20and%20potential%20limitations%20that%20you%20experience%20in%20your%20everyday%20life.%20As%20a%209-year-old%2C%20you%20can%20pretend%20that%20you're%2011.%20You%20can%20try%20things%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20sites%20were%20made%20for%20children%2C%20they%20were%20heavily%20moderated.%20Club%20Penguin%20blocked%20swearing%20and%20words%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Baddress%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bschool%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bphone%20number%26quot%3B%20from%20chats%20to%20prevent%20users%20from%20sharing%20identifiable%20information.%20Parents%20could%20also%20use%20an%20%26quot%3BUltimate%20Safe%20Chat%26quot%3B%20option%20that%20allowed%20their%20child%20to%20interact%20with%20others%20only%20by%20choosing%20from%20a%20list%20of%20pre-written%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20many%20parents%20worried%20about%20who%20their%20kids%20were%20talking%20to%20online%20%E2%80%94%20fears%20that%20weren't%20completely%20unfounded.%20Several%20online%20stores%20stopped%20selling%20gift%20cards%20for%20the%20popular%20virtual%20world%20Habbo%20Hotel%20in%202012%20after%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.itv.com%2Fnews%2F2012-06-12%2Fhabbo-hotel-children-site-labelled-a-paedophile-haven%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20lapses%20in%20moderation%20that%20allowed%20explicit%20sexual%20messages%20to%20slip%20through.%20Following%20the%20revelation%2C%20one%20of%20the%20firm's%20key%20investors%20backed%20out%2C%20and%20over%20half%20of%20the%20game's%209%20million%20monthly%20users%20left%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20websites%20didn't%20experience%20such%20a%20dramatic%20loss%20of%20users.%20Instead%2C%20it%20was%20a%20gradual%20decline%20as%20kids%20turned%20their%20attention%20to%20newer%2C%20shiner%20distractions.%20As%20smartphones%20took%20over%20in%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20people%20started%20to%20play%20around%20on%20their%20phones%20instead%20of%20their%20desktops%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fangry-birds-sales-numbers-2011-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emobile%20games%20like%20Angry%20Birds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Temple%20Run%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflappy-birds-2014-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlappy%20Bird%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20off.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20online%20kids'%20websites%2C%20many%20of%20which%20weren't%20compatible%20with%20smartphones%2C%20started%20to%20die%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20tried%20to%20keep%20up.%20In%202017%20it%20shut%20down%20Club%20Penguin%20and%20replaced%20it%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-club-penguin-island-launch-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emobile%20version%2C%20Club%20Penguin%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20never%20quite%20caught%20on%20and%20was%20discontinued%20a%20year%20later.%20Toontown%20shut%20down%20in%202013.%20Moshi%20Monsters%20ceased%20operations%20in%202019.%20While%20sites%20like%20Webkinz%2C%20Wizard101%2C%20and%20Neopets%20remain%20active%2C%20they've%20become%20ghost%20towns%20compared%20to%20what%20they%20used%20to%20be.%20The%20brief%2C%20exhilarating%20world%20of%20my%20childhood%20couldn't%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20kids%20spend%20their%20time%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-roblox-is-so-popular-and-how-it-works-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoblox%3C%2Fa%3E%20(some%2080%20million%20daily%20active%20users)%2C%20an%20online%20platform%20that%20allows%20users%20to%20design%20and%20play%20games%20created%20by%20others%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-people-play-forthttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-people-play-fortnite-2018-11nite-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFortnite%3C%2Fa%3E%20(100%20million%20monthly%20active%20users)%2C%20a%20gaming%20platform%20that%20includes%20everything%20from%20survival%20games%20to%20Guitar%20Hero%20look-alikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20these%20virtual%20words%20are%20similar%20to%20the%20games%20of%20my%20own%20childhood%3A%20They%20provide%20a%20space%20for%20children%20to%20escape%20the%20stresses%20of%20everyday%20life%20while%20interacting%20with%20others%20in%20a%20safe%2C%20moderated%20environment.%20Priebe%20referred%20to%20them%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrandchildren%20of%20Club%20Penguin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Maleno%2C%20the%2020-year-old%20who%20grew%20up%20playing%20MMOs%2C%20doesn't%20believe%20Fortnite%20and%20Roblox%20games%20were%20designed%20for%20younger%20audiences.%20%26quot%3BThe%20streamers%20are%20adults%2C%20the%20content%20creators%20are%20adults%2C%20the%20skins%20you%20purchase%20in-game%20are%20adults%2C%20and%20it's%20permeated%20with%20violence%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20cartoon%20violence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20about%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20Fortnite%20games%2C%20Fortnite%20Battle%20Royale.%20In%20separate%20statements%2C%20spokespeople%20from%20Fortnite%20and%20Roblox%20told%20me%20that%20the%20games%20have%20robust%20child-safety%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20aren't%20battling%20it%20out%20on%20Fortnite%2C%20children%20are%20increasingly%20on%20social%20media.%20In%202021%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-under-13-use-facebook-instagram-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20kids%20under%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%20already%20use%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook.%20And%20in%202020%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F08%2F14%2Ftechnology%2Ftiktok-underage-users-ftc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20third%20of%20TikTok's%20US%20users%20may%20be%2014%20or%20under.%26quot%3B%20This%20became%20apparent%20in%20May%20when%20a%20TikTok%20of%20a%20young%20girl's%20%26quot%3Bget%20ready%20with%20me%26quot%3B%20clip%20went%20viral%20before%20being%20deleted.%20Many%20commenters%20thought%20the%20girl%20was%20too%20young%20to%20be%20using%20the%20platform%2C%20while%20others%20criticized%20her%20for%20wearing%20makeup.%20Some%20suggested%20that%20she%20was%20taking%20part%20in%20activities%20designed%20for%20adults%20because%20she%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20others%20on%20the%20platform%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reaction%20to%20the%20video%20underscored%20the%20absence%20of%20online%20spaces%20made%20exclusively%20for%20children.%20Instead%20of%20playing%20with%20toys%20or%20games%2C%20concerned%20observers%20argued%20that%20today's%20young%20people%20are%20being%20exposed%20to%20content%20primarily%20created%20for%20adults%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshley%20Hernandez%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20art%20educator%20who%20works%20with%20children%20of%20various%20ages%20across%20New%20York%20City%2C%20has%20a%20different%20take.%20She%20doesn't%20think%20the%20adult%20spaces%20are%20necessarily%20harming%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20she%20argued%20that%20children%20mimicking%20adult%20behaviors%20in%20media%20is%20nothing%20new.%20Children%20have%20always%20tried%20to%20imitate%20adults%20by%20playing%20house%20or%20role-playing%20adult%20professions%20such%20as%20doctors%20and%20nurses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20people%20might%20be%20amplifying%20the%20adultification%20of%20young%20people%20because%20they're%20so%20stuck%20in%20the%20differences%20between%20generations%20and%20struggle%20on%20seeing%20the%20similarities%2C%26quot%3B%20Hernandez%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20would%20understand%20that%20we're%20not%20as%20different%20as%20we%20think%20if%20adults%20tried%20to%20understand%20young%20people%20more%20and%20have%20more%20in-depth%20conversations%20and%20actually%20listen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20romanticize%20the%20past%20and%20gloss%20over%20what%20we%20were%20exposed%20to%20as%20children.%20I%20remember%20countless%20incidents%20of%20people%20trying%20to%20get%20past%20chat%20censors%20on%20MMOs%20by%20intentionally%20misspelling%20offensive%20words%20or%20by%20replacing%20letters%20with%20numbers.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20think%20anything%20of%20it%2C%20and%20I%20still%20don't.%20It's%20normal%20for%20children%20to%20push%20boundaries%20to%20see%20what%20they%20can%20get%20away%20with.%20And%20while%20I'll%20never%20really%20know%20if%20my%20online%20friends%20were%20who%20they%20said%20they%20were%2C%20my%20interactions%20with%20them%20definitely%20left%20a%20positive%20impact.%20Even%20when%20things%20in%20my%20personal%20life%20felt%20difficult%2C%20it%20was%20comforting%20to%20know%20I%20could%20rely%20on%20my%20online%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20generation%20is%20partial%20to%20what%20was%20hot%20when%20they%20were%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20and%20skeptical%20of%20everything%20that%20comes%20after.%20For%20my%20generation%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20as%20the%20internet%20gained%20mainstream%20acceptance%2C%20this%20cycle%20of%20nostalgia%20appears%20to%20have%20accelerated.%20Tough%20market%20competition%20and%20higher%20consumer%20expectations%20have%20forced%20innovation%2C%20leading%20to%20shorter%20product%20cycles%20and%20more%20frequent%20releases.%20This%20means%20there's%20always%20something%20newer%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20better%20for%20us%20to%20move%20on%20to.%20Of%20course%2C%20each%20time%20we%20move%20on%2C%20we%20leave%20a%20part%20of%20us%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20surprising%20now%20is%20just%20how%20quickly%20my%20cohort%20of%2020-somethings%20are%20trying%20to%20return%20to%20our%20origins.%20In%202017%2C%20Neopets%20was%20bought%20by%20the%20Chinese%20firm%20NetDragon.%20When%20the%20entrepreneur%20and%20investing%20consultant%20Dominic%20Law%20joined%20the%20company%20in%202020%2C%20he%20began%20an%20internal%20campaign%20to%20revive%20the%20brand.%20In%20the%20six%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20April%2C%20the%20number%20of%20monthly%20users%20tripled.%20Over%20half%20of%20the%20players%20were%20over%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20suggesting%20that%20many%20had%20been%20pulled%20back%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnostalgia-key-to-happiness-creativity-innovation-future-change-progress-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enostalgia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20much%20effort%20the%20new%20owners%20of%20Neopets%20put%20into%20reviving%20the%20website%2C%20I%20doubt%20it'll%20ever%20be%20the%20bustling%20community%20hub%20that%20it%20once%20was.%20But%20for%20those%20who%20grew%20up%20with%20it%2C%20logging%20into%20Neopia%20is%20a%20rare%20opportunity%20to%20dip%20back%20into%20their%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nostalgia%20we%20feel%20for%20these%20online%20communities%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20how%20much%20they%20impacted%20our%20formative%20years.%20Despite%20being%20completely%20virtual%2C%20they%20provided%20a%20space%20for%20us%20to%20learn%20about%20ourselves%20and%20grow.%20It's%20only%20natural%20that%20we%20sometimes%20feel%20the%20pull%20to%20try%20to%20recreate%20these%20experiences%20as%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20cycle%20will%20continue.%20Just%20as%20my%20cohort%20fondly%20recalls%20Neopets%20and%20Furry%20Paws%2C%20kids%20today%20will%20make%20nostalgic%20memes%20about%20Fortnite%20and%20Roblox.%20In%20five%20years%2C%20it%20will%20be%20something%20entirely%20new.%20Instead%20of%20the%20permanent%20internet%20that%20was%20touted%20when%20we%20were%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20put%20online%20will%20haunt%20you%20forever!%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20we're%20stuck%20with%20a%20quickly%20evolving%20realm%20that%20risks%20sucking%20our%20childhoods%20into%20oblivion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faimee-pearcy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAimee%20Pearcy%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20who%20writes%20about%20technology%20and%20digital%20culture.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-childhood-internet-gone-club-penguin-neopets-webkinz-nostalgia-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722505562000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a00230fb2b6bedb059c21e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-childhood-internet-gone-club-penguin-neopets-webkinz-nostalgia-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Millennials%20were%20raised%20by%20the%20internet.%20Now%20their%20internet%20parents%20are%20gone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aimee.pearcy%40gmail.com%20(Aimee%20Pearcy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com