%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERachel%20Hoobing%20(not%20pictured)%20said%20she%20didn't%20realize%20that%20blue-collar%20work%20was%20a%20viable%20career%20choice%20when%20she%20was%20growing%20up.%3Cp%3ECredit%3A%20Getty%20Images%2Fserts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERachel%20Hoobing%20went%20to%20college%20and%20tried%20several%20white-collar%20jobs%20in%20her%2020s%20and%2030s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20decided%20to%20become%20an%20electrician%20at%2043%20and%20trained%20at%20a%20community%20college%20and%20with%20a%20union.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHoobing%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20wished%20she'd%20started%20that%20career%20sooner.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Rachel%20Hoobing%2C%20a%2050-year-old%20electrician%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20always%20encouraged%20to%20take%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20father%20was%20a%20pastor%2C%20and%20my%20mom%20worked%20in%20schools.%20I'd%20felt%20a%20lot%20of%20classism%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblue-collar%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20college%20to%20study%20biology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectrician-switched-medicine-surgeon-degree-college-pre-med-gen-z-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetermined%20to%20be%20a%20doctor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20I%20was%20there%2C%20I%20decided%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20physical%20therapist%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20finished%20my%20degree%20in%201995%20and%20applied%20to%20physical%20therapy%20schools.%20I%20didn't%20get%20into%20any%2C%20so%20I%20tried%20again%20the%20following%20year%20and%20failed%20again.%20It%20was%20competitive%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20had%20the%20right%20skills%20for%20the%20exam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225edd072c-1024-4d95-a3df-f4eb9b8ed5fa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20floundering%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20two%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20my%20life.%20I%20lived%20at%20home%20with%20my%20parents%20and%20pieced%20together%20some%20work%20doing%20elder%20care%20locally.%20There%20weren't%20a%20lot%20of%20opportunities%20in%20the%20small%20town%20I%20was%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201997%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20become%20a%20pastor%20like%20my%20father%20and%20went%20to%20seminary%20for%20four%20years%20to%20train%20in%20theology.%20A%20year%20and%20a%20half%20into%20the%20four-year%20course%2C%20I%20decided%20being%20a%20pastor%20wasn't%20for%20me.%20I%20switched%20my%20course%20and%20graduated%20with%20a%20master's%20in%20theology%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20nanny%20for%20a%20while.%20I%20was%20grateful%20for%20the%20work%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20my%20life.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20floundering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20try%20teaching%20in%202006.%20After%20my%20teacher%20training%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20an%20elementary%20school.%20The%20long%20hours%20and%20classroom%20management%20stressed%20me%20out.%20I%20had%20nightmares%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20failing.%20I%20was%20only%20a%20teacher%20for%20two%20months.%20I%20hated%20working%20at%20a%20desk%20sometimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238fa774f-54de-4c47-902b-bb707079dcd3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20quit%20my%20job%20to%20become%20an%20electrician%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20I%20got%20a%20temporary%20job%20at%20the%20Jobs%20Corps%2C%20a%20national%20program%20run%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor.%20I%20helped%20people%20transition%20into%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20trades%2C%20from%20arborists%20to%20nurse%20assistants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20there%20was%20a%20whole%20different%20job%20market%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20with%20a%20career%20counselor.%20They%20helped%20me%20realize%20that%2C%20ever%20since%20I%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20I'd%20enjoyed%20fixing%2C%20designing%2C%20and%20building%20things.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20I%20was%20in%20my%2040s.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20start%20a%20career%20where%20I%20might%20risk%20busting%20my%20shoulder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20casework%20at%20the%20Job%20Corps.%20I%20found%20it%20very%20stressful%20and%20decided%20to%20leave%20in%20May%202012%20and%20apply%20for%20an%20electrician%20apprenticeship.%20I%20didn't%20get%20in%2C%20and%20it%20was%20terrifying.%20I%20had%20to%20wait%20two%20years%20before%20I%20could%20apply%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280313441-2186-4bd3-9732-ee0350013c99%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20took%20classes%20at%20a%20community%20college%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20I%20took%20some%20electrical%20work%20classes%20at%20the%20local%20community%20college%20while%20working%20part-time%20at%20Home%20Depot%20and%20doing%20odd%20jobs.%20I%20was%20just%20trying%20to%20survive%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20I%20got%20my%20electrical%20trainee%20card%2C%20which%20meant%20I%20could%20do%20some%20non-union%20work%20as%20an%20electrician.%20I%20started%20working%20with%20an%20electrician%20who%20installed%20EV%20chargers.%20I%20had%20a%20portfolio%20of%20my%20work%20from%20the%20classes%20and%20practiced%20for%20the%20apprenticeship%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20an%20electrical%20apprenticeship%20with%20a%20union%20in%202016%2C%20when%20I%20was%2043%2C%20and%20started%20the%20following%20year.%20T